(131, 1, '2015-08-26 00:53:11', '2015-08-26 00:53:11', '\r\n\r\n									<div itemprop="video" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/VideoObject">\r\n<h2><span itemprop="name">All on Four Dental Implants</span> Explained:</h2>\r\n<p>     <meta itemprop="duration" content="T04M39S"><meta itemprop="thumbnailUrl" content="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/8pn3eV8euwU/hqdefault.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentURL" content="https://www.youtube.com/v/8pn3eV8euwU"><meta itemprop="embedURL" content="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8pn3eV8euwU"><br>\r\n     <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8pn3eV8euwU?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;controls=1&amp;autohide=1" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="197" width="351"></iframe><br>\r\n     </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>Living with the stigma that comes with missing teeth? Too embarrassed to be seen in public without your full smile?</p>\r\n<p>For many years dentures have been the preferred solution for the replacement of missing teeth:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Complete dentures are used by people who have lost all their natural upper or lower teeth.</li>\r\n<li>Partial dentures are for patients who still retain some of their natural teeth.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Although dentures are still popular, Dental Implants are quickly becoming one of the most sought after tooth replacement options today. Replicating a missing tooth root, Dental Implants are fine titanium screws or rods that are placed into the jawbone.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The latest innovation in modern dentistry- All-on-4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bringing dentures and dental implants together, All-On-4 Implant Retained Dentures, enable patients to have a set of upper or lower dentures permanently secured, sometimes with as few as four Dental Implants.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How is this achieved?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Simply by placing two of the four implants at an angle at the front of the mouth where the jawbone is denser and stronger.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How do I maintain my All-on-4 Implant Retained Dentures?</strong></p>\r\n<p>After receiving your All-on-4 Implant Retained Dentures, it is essential you follow a thorough at-home brushing and flossing routine. You should also schedule regular appointment check-ups every six months with Dr Yassmin to ensure your implants remain strong.</p>\r\n<p>To learn more about <strong>All-on-4</strong> and find out if youâ€™re an ideal candidate to use them, schedule a consultation appointment with Dr Yassmin who will explain the procedure in non-medical terms and gladly answer any of your questions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note:</strong> Any surgical or invasive procedure carries risks. Before proceeding, you should seek a second opinion from an appropriately qualified health practitioner.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n									\r\n								', 'ALL-ON-4', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'all-on-4-2', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:29:18', '2015-09-04 05:29:18', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?page_id=131', 0, 'page', '', 0),
