(479, 1, '2015-09-02 03:22:16', '2015-09-02 03:22:16', '<h2>Sydney Dentist Dr Fadi Yassmin is featured on Cosmo Bride</h2>\r\n<h1>SAY CHEESE</h1>\r\nGet teeth that sparkle whiter than a Hollywood starâ€™s with the latest technology in dental town.\r\nINVISALIGN\r\nDr. Fadi Yassmin of Broadway Dental (broadwaydental.com.au) explains.\r\nThe Treatment\r\nIt uses a series of clear aligners to gradually move teeth into position. Theyâ€™re made of non-toxic, virtually invisible plastic.\r\nHow It Works\r\nThe alignersneed to be on for around 22 hours per day (except when eating). Each one is worn for a period of two weeks, at which point you switch to the next aligner in the series.\r\nHow It Feels\r\nAligners are tight when you first put them on, but pain isnâ€™t a common complaint.\r\nThe Results\r\nThe average treatment takes 12 to 14 months. Youâ€™ll probably notice aesthetic changes in the first three months.\r\nCost\r\nExpect to pay $6000 to $8500. Check with your health fund to see if youâ€™re covered.', 'Say Cheese', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'say-cheese', '', '', '2015-09-02 08:41:42', '2015-09-02 08:41:42', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?post_type=article&#038;p=479', 0, 'article', '', 0),
