(483, 1, '2015-09-02 03:24:46', '2015-09-02 03:24:46', '<h2>As an experienced Sydney Dentist, Dr Fadi Yassmin shares with Primped readers the benefits of teeth whitening</h2>\r\n<h1>THE TRUTH, THE WHOLE TRUTH AND NOTHING BUT THE TRUTH ABOUT TEETH WHITENING</h1>\r\nOnce upon a time, teeth whitening used to be the domain of the rich and famous, but these days, everyone from your Nan to your neighbour is getting in on the act. So, to find out more, we hit up Sydney cosmetic dentist, Dr Fadi Yassmin for more info.\r\nAshley Green sure knows the power of pearly whites.\r\nWhat causes our pegs to discolour? Everyoneâ€™s teeth have a different base colour to begin with but things like coffee, tea, red wine, cigarettes and some medication will cause teeth to discolour.\r\nCan you explain how whitening works?\r\nThe exact mechanism is not fully understood but itâ€™s mostly attributed to an oxidation reaction. Hydrogen peroxide is the most commonly used agent and it works by penetrating the enamel to cause a colour change by removing both extrinsic and intrinsic stains.\r\nWhatâ€™s better, laser or at-home brightening kits?\r\nInstant whitening is more effective mostly because at-home kits rely on patient compliance â€“ you have to remember to wear the trays! Itâ€™s also important to remember that all whitening procedures need to be maintained with regular top ups using at-home in trays.\r\nAre there any side effects?\r\nSensitivity is the main side effect for teeth whitening but this can be overcome with the use of products like a mousse that are designed to desensitise the teeth prior to treatment, during and post treatment.\r\nIs teeth whitening a no no for people with sensitive teeth?\r\nIf youâ€™ve got sensitive teeth, we recommend you opt for instant teeth whitening, only after a course of the teeth mousse treatment the week prior. That way, the whitening is done in one go and any sensitivity will not last for as long as it would if you were doing the take home whitening kits which usually take two weeks.\r\nWhatâ€™s the downside of teeth whitening?\r\nPost treatment, itâ€™s vital that you avoid eating and drinking anything that stains for at least 48 hours. Think red wine, tea, curry, berries and of course, cigarettes.\r\nHow long does it take to see results?\r\nWith instant whitening you will see the results as soon as you step out of the surgery and with take home kits you start to see the difference within a few days but maximum results are after 2 weeks.\r\nWhatâ€™s your best advice for getting the most out of the treatment?\r\nAvoid food and drinks that discolour teeth (cromogenic foods i.e coffee, tea, curry, berries) and committing to regular at-home maintenance kits will do the trick.\r\nHave you had your teeth whitened?\r\nDo you use an at-home whitening kit?\r\nWhatâ€™s more important to you â€“ bright pegs or straight teeth?\r\nDr Fadi Yassmin can be found at Broadway Dental. For more info on cosmetic dentistry, teeth whitening, or smile makeovers checkout broadwaydental.com.au or call on (02) 9281 0100.\r\nPrimped â€“ Blush Hour, acting editor Eliza Ashe\r\n', 'The truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth about teeth whitening', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-truth-the-whole-truth-and-nothing-but-the-truth-about-teeth-whitening', '', '', '2015-09-02 08:37:52', '2015-09-02 08:37:52', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?post_type=article&#038;p=483', 0, 'article', '', 0),
