(487, 1, '2015-09-02 03:27:14', '2015-09-02 03:27:14', '<h2>Dr Fadi Yassmin of Sydney dental practice, Broadway Dental explains Britesmile technology</h2>\r\n<h1>THE HOLLYWOOD SMILE</h1>\r\nCelebrities helped to coin the term â€œHollywood smileâ€ when they started walked the red carpet with megawatt grins. But if youâ€™re a fan of coffee, red wine, fizzy drinks and donâ€™t always floss, you might need a little helping hand in getting an A-list smile.\r\nBriteSmile is one of the best teeth lightening treatments that weâ€™ve tried. Itâ€™s suitable for those with sensitive teeth (you might just need to use a mousse in the week leading up to your treatment) and helps to lift stains from the teeth in four hours with instant results, making it a great option for those whoâ€™ve left it to the last minute. Although we would ordinarily recommend you have the treatment at least a week out in the unlikely event that you experience any sensitivity.\r\nWe tried BriteSmile (approx $995) at Broadway Dental with Dr. Fadi Yassmin\r\nPosted by Sarah Macrae Bellasugar Australia\r\nPictured: Mandy Moore at last yearâ€™s Oscars\r\nImage Source: Getty', 'The Hollywood Smile', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-hollywood-smile', '', '', '2015-09-02 08:26:44', '2015-09-02 08:26:44', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?post_type=article&#038;p=487', 0, 'article', '', 0),
