(493, 1, '2015-09-02 03:32:15', '2015-09-02 03:32:15', '<h1>TEETH TALK: HOW TO GET A MILLION DOLLAR-LOOKING SMILE, WITHOUT BRACES</h1>\r\nEverybody has their â€˜thing.â€™ For some people, itâ€™s having perfect hair, for others, it might be manicured nails, or glowing skin. For me, having straight, pearly whites has always been high on my beauty agenda. But what does one do when theyâ€™re way past the age and stage of braces and looking for a discrete way to get a million-dollar-looking smile? To find out, I hit up Dr Fadi Yassmin at Broadway Dental Centre in Sydney to deliver the facts.\r\nQ. Is it true that teeth move every 7 years?\r\nTeeth can potentially move all the time, there are many different reasons for this- forces from everyday chewing to excessive clenching and erupting wisdom teeth can also contribute to tooth movement.\r\nQ. What are the alternatives to braces?\r\nThe alternative is to use sequential plastic aligners, the most advanced system by far is Invisalign.\r\nQ. Are the results from these alternative procedures as effective as traditional braces?\r\nThere are cases that it can actually be faster treating with Invisalign than with conventional braces. Most cases can be treated as well as with conventional braces.\r\nQ. Do straightening treatments like Invisalign work on all clients?\r\nSometimes itâ€™s a matter of being able to do the Invisalign treatment with a combination of other treatment methods to boost the process.\r\nQ. Whatâ€™s the difference between an Orthodontist and a Cosmetic Dentist?\r\nAn orthodontist focuses only on the straightening of teeth and occlusion where as a good cosmetic dentist that does orthodontic treatment will not only look at the alignment of the teeth, the occlusion, but also what is most aesthetic, focusing on the symmetry and shape of the final smile.\r\nQ. What credentials should we look for when choosing a dentist/orthodontist?\r\nThe obvious thing is that the dentist or orthodontist has all of their university training but things like checking that the dentist keeps up to date with the latest technologies and techniques are important. The other really big thing is to check the dentists experience, checking that they are a platinum elite provider for Invisalign and checking their body of work by way of other patients treatment photos.\r\nQ. What does Invisalign involve and how long does the treatment plan generally take?\r\nIf the patient is deemed suitable (provided that general dental health is fine) for Invisalign then diagnostic scans, models and photos are taken and a treatment plan is entered by the dentist and all the information is sent to Invisalign. Once the Information is received then a carefully constructed 3D simulation of the dentists requests are constructed, at this stage the dentist is able to make changes to the treatment plan for final outcome. The aligners will come back from Invisalign and treatment begins.\r\nQ. How do you maintain the results once the treatment process is finished?\r\nRetainers will need to be worn once the treatment is complete, the type of retainer will vary depending on the case. All orthodontic treatment whether conventional or Invisalign will need some retention as teeth have a memory and with time will move back into position.\r\nOver to you know Primpettesâ€¦\r\nHave you had braces?\r\nHave you tried Invisalign?\r\nWould you like to have your teeth straightened?\r\nDr Fadi Yassmin leads the friendly team with great smiles at Broadway Dental. For more info on cosmetic dentistry, teeth whitening, or smile makeovers checkout broadwaydental.com.au or call on (02) 9281 0100.\r\nPrimped â€“ Blush Hour, acting editor Eliza Ashe', 'Teeth Talk: How to Get a Million Dollar-Looking Smile, Without Braces', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'teeth-talk-how-to-get-a-million-dollar-looking-smile-without-braces', '', '', '2015-09-02 08:16:23', '2015-09-02 08:16:23', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?post_type=article&#038;p=493', 0, 'article', '', 0),
