(695, 1, '2015-09-04 05:43:21', '2015-09-04 05:43:21', '<h2>The Treatment You Need<br>Without The Pain</h2>\r\n<div class="text">\r\n\r\n									<p><iframe width="390" height="219" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/fNEXBiPsF5E?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;controls=1&amp;autohide=1"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>For some people the overwhelming fear of dental appointments can cause anxiety and lead to postponing much needed treatment. This may stem from previous bad experiences, a misunderstanding of dental procedures or a lack of knowledge of modern treatments and options.</p>\r\n<p>The comfort, relaxation and happiness of our patients is foremost for Dr Yassmin, and the entire Broadway Dental team will do whatever they can to reduce your anxiety, alleviate any fears and provide painless, quick treatments.</p>\r\n<p><strong>One such option is Sleep Dentistry.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Often referred to as pain free dentistry, twilight sedation, dental sedation or sedation dentistry, this innovative form of sedation dentistry is a safe and highly effective technique used to overcome the fear, anxiety and discomfort that so often accompanies a visit to the dentist.</p>\r\n<p>Sleep Dentistry combines sedative and pain relieving medication which, is intravenously administered and supervised by an experienced medical doctor and has patients virtually asleep throughout the entire procedure.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When should Sleep Dentistry be applied?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sleep Dentistry is recommended for patients who:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dislike needles,</li>\r\n<li>Have a low pain threshold,</li>\r\n<li>Have difficulty getting numb,</li>\r\n<li>Dislike noises, smells and tastes associated with dental treatments,</li>\r\n<li>Have gag reflexes,</li>\r\n<li>Present jaw problems,</li>\r\n<li>Require long treatment sessions,</li>\r\n<li>Are undergoing a lengthy procedure or wish to complete several procedures in a single appointment visit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sleep Dentistry can take the anxiety out of your dental procedure or help you complete several procedures at once so you get the treatment you need and the beautiful healthy smile you have always wanted.</p>\r\n<p>Ask us how you can sleep through your next dental visit and wake up with a gorgeous smile.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									', 'Sleep Dentistry', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '214-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:43:21', '2015-09-04 05:43:21', '', 214, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/214-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(696, 1, '2015-09-04 05:45:58', '2015-09-04 05:45:58', '<h2>getting a good nightâ€™s sleep</h2>\r\n\r\n									<p><iframe width="390" height="219" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/gheJfAQRgcA?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;controls=1&amp;autohide=1" style="padding-bottom: 20px;"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>How many times do you get elbowed every night to stop you from snoring? </strong></p>\r\n<p>If the answer is far too many, you need to look into it.</p>\r\n<p>Snoring is not only disruptive for a sleeping partner, it may be an indicator of the serious condition known as Obstructive Sleep Apnoea (OSA).</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is Obstructive Sleep Apnoea?</strong></p>\r\n<p>OSA is a condition that occurs when the soft tissue and muscles at the back of the throat relax while you sleep. As a result the air passage becomes blocked and breathing is paused.</p>\r\n<p>These non-breathing episodes can last anywhere from 10 seconds up to one minute. In severe cases they can occur several hundred times per night.</p>\r\n<p>When the person with OSA stops breathing, their brain registers the lack of oxygen and sends a signal to the throat muscles causing the snorer to jolt, wake up, start breathing again and fall back to sleep almost immediately. In fact, most OSA sufferers donâ€™t even have a recollection of ever waking up.</p>\r\n<p>Obstructive Sleep Apnoea is a serious medical condition. It can cause daytime fatigue due to disruptive sleep patterns, contribute to high blood pressure, heart disease and stroke.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What causes Obstructive Sleep Apnoea?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Contributing factors to OSA include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Being overweight,</li>\r\n<li>Smoking and,</li>\r\n<li>Excessive consumption of alcohol.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>How can OSA be reversed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>A significant weight loss can often reduce the severity of snoring and Sleep Apnoea.</p>\r\n<p>A dental night splint is also a very useful tool to assist with the reversal of Sleep Apnoea.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is a Dental Night Splint?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Similar to a sport mouthguard, a dental splint repositions the jaw, helping to open the air passage and facilitating easier breathing during sleep.</p>\r\n<p>If you or your partner snore or stop breathing during sleep, itâ€™s important for you to schedule a consultation appointment with the Broadway Dental team.</p>\r\n<p>Dr Yassmin will assess the positioning of your jaw while itâ€™s relaxed and determine if your OSA symptoms could be resolved with the use of a night splint.</p>\r\n<p>If you require an in-depth sleep study, you will be referred to one of the select group of specialists who work with Broadway Dental.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n						', 'Sleep Apnoea', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:45:58', '2015-09-04 05:45:58', '', 240, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/240-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(697, 1, '2015-09-04 05:49:17', '2015-09-04 05:49:17', '<h1>WHAT IS ALL ON 4 DENTAL IMPLANT</h1>\r\n\r\n									<p><img width="277" height="184" data-id="2666" src="http://broadwaydental.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/a_03.jpg" alt="a_03" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-2666 space">What is All On 4 dental implant?</p>\r\n<p>The All-On-4 system offered at our Dental Clinic is a new innovation in implant dentistry, which brings a dental prosthesis and dental implants together.</p>\r\n<p>A dental implant is a fine titanium screw or rod placed into the jaw bone during a minor surgical procedure to replace a missing tooth root. Titanium is a strong bio-compatible alloy and has been used successfully in reconstructive medicine for many years as it naturally integrates with bone.</p>\r\n<p>Previously, a single dental implant was placed vertically and used to replace a single tooth or support a dental bridge of up to three teeth. To support an entire upper or lower arch of teeth, up to eight dental implants were necessary.</p>\r\n<p>The All-On-4 System enables you to have a set of upper or lower prosthetic teeth permanently secured, often with as few as four dental implants.</p>\r\n<p>The treatment is made possible because two of the implants are slightly longer than traditional dental implants. They are also placed at an acute angle at the front of the mouth where your jaw bone is denser and stronger, and provides the greatest support for your prosthesis.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n', 'Whats is All On 4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '187-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:49:17', '2015-09-04 05:49:17', '', 187, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/187-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(698, 1, '2015-09-04 05:52:25', '2015-09-04 05:52:25', '<h1>Restoring Smile with All on 4 Procedure</h1>\r\n\r\n									<p>If you have loose and uncomfortable removable dentures, have a bridge, are losing or missing teeth, All-On-4 may be the perfect permanent restorative solution for your smile.</p>\r\n<p>The All-On-4 System available at Broadway Dental allows you to replace your removable dentures or missing teeth with a permanently secured prosthesis.</p>\r\n<p>One of the main advantages of the All-On-4 System, is only a very small percentage of people are unsuitable for this procedure. If you no-longer wish to wear loose and uncomfortable dentures, have been told youâ€™re unsuitable for dental implants, are missing teeth or want a permanent bridge replacement, then the All-on-4 System may be the perfect restorative solution for you.</p>\r\n<p>Dr Fadi Yassmin is a leading authority on implant dentistry. Many patients come to, or are referred to Dr Yassmin and the team at Broadway Dental for assessment and advice on the best treatment options to restore their smile through the All-On-4 System.</p>\r\n<p>The All-On-4 System lets you enjoy all the benefits of having a full upper and lower arch of permanently secured prosthetic teeth and a healthy, perfect smile.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									', 'ALL on 4 Procedure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '201-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:52:25', '2015-09-04 05:52:25', '', 201, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/201-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(699, 1, '2015-09-04 05:54:58', '2015-09-04 05:54:58', '<h1>ALL on 4 Benefits</h1>\n', 'Benifits of All On 4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '190-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:54:58', '2015-09-04 05:54:58', '', 190, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/190-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(700, 1, '2015-09-04 05:55:36', '2015-09-04 05:55:36', '<h1>ALL on 4 Benefits</h1>\r\n\r\n									<h4>Throw away your old dentures</h4>\r\n<p>For many people dentures are cumbersome, uncomfortable and constantly loose, making them feel uneasy about smiling and eating, while missing teeth can compromise on your oral and general health.</p>\r\n<h2>Why All On 4?</h2>\r\n<p>There are many benefits to choosing the All-On-4 System. Some include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>They look, feel and function just like natural teeth</li>\r\n<li>Aid in helping to keep your jaw bone strong</li>\r\n<li>Virtually eliminates the need for bone grafting, which is invasive, and adds to recovery time</li>\r\n<li>Easy to clean and maintain good oral health</li>\r\n<li>Less expensive than traditional dental implants as fewer implants are required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br>\r\nThe All-On-4 System from Broadway Dental can give you a complete smile once again and help you regain your confidence. Unlike a denture which is held by adhesive and a bridge, which relies on healthy teeth for support, the All-On-4 System of prosthetics is permanently secured with dental implants.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>', 'Benifits of All On 4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '190-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:55:36', '2015-09-04 05:55:36', '', 190, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/190-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(701, 1, '2015-09-04 06:00:12', '2015-09-04 06:00:12', '\r\n\r\n									<p>What is pre-operative care in All On Four procedure? This is the most important phase of your treatment. Ensuring you are in good oral health can help reduce recovery time and aid in long-term success.</p>\r\n<p>Dr Yassmin will take the time to explain the procedure in detail, develop a tailored treatment plan and answer all of your questions.</p>\r\n<p>The first step is to have a comprehensive examination of your oral health to determine your suitability. General health conditions such as diabetes, oral health conditions such as gum disease and lifestyle decisions such as smoking can all cause complications and affect the success of the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>Your tooth roots are responsible for keeping your jaw bone strong and healthy. If you have been missing teeth for some time, itâ€™s possible to have lost some bone density and volume.</p>\r\n<p>A 3-D CT (CAT) scan is taken and produces a highly detailed image of your bone structure. This is used to evaluate your bone quality and density. Then advanced computer imaging software is used to plan your surgery and ensure precise placement of your implants.</p>\r\n<p>The final stage involves creating detailed impression moulds of your gum line and taking photographs. These will ensure your new smile looks natural and your new prosthetic teeth bite together perfectly.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n', 'Pre - Operative Care', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '192-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 06:00:12', '2015-09-04 06:00:12', '', 192, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/192-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(702, 1, '2015-09-04 06:03:11', '2015-09-04 06:03:11', '\r\n\r\n								<h1>All on 4 Treatment Process</h1>\r\n\r\n								\r\n					\r\n									<p style="text-align: left;"><img width="300" height="156" data-id="2677" src="http://broadwaydental.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/DnetureFree4Life_Microsite_TreatmentProcess_HTML_03-300x156.jpg" alt="Dental Implant Treatment Process" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-2677">Placing your dental implants is a minimally invasive procedure that can be completed in a single appointment here at the Broadway Dental purpose-built All-on-4 clinic.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Every surgery is unique and will be tailored to your specific needs and circumstance.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Receiving your implants can take between three and six hours. The expected timeframe to place all of your implants is reliant on many factors and will be discussed with you in detail during your assessment appointments.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">To ensure youâ€™re completely comfortable at all times, Broadway Dental offers several pain relief options including local anaesthetic and IV Sedation, sometimes referred to as <a href="http://broadwaydental.com.au/treatments/sleep-dentistry/" title="Sleep Dentistry">Sleep Dentistry</a>.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">After making a small incision in the gum, and using a special customised guide, each implant is placed into its precise location in the jaw bone.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Once your implants are in place, a temporary set of prosthetic teeth are secured. Once your implants have completely bonded to your jaw bone, you will receive your permanent set of prosthetic teeth.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n							', 'The Treatment Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '194-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 06:03:11', '2015-09-04 06:03:11', '', 194, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/194-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(703, 1, '2015-09-04 06:10:49', '2015-09-04 06:10:49', '\r\n\r\n								<h1>All on 4 Recovery Process</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n									<p>Everyone is different and your complete recovery will depend on your oral and general health. Most people are able to return to work and their normal daily routine the following day, however, the average time for implants to integrate fully with your jaw bone is four to six months.</p>\r\n<p>Biting and chewing places extreme pressure on your teeth and gums. It is advised to have a soft food diet for at least two months after receiving your implants. If you experience any discomfort it can be relieved with a cold compress and over-the-counter medication.</p>\r\n<p>You may also be required to visit our clinic one week, four weeks and 12 weeks after your procedure so Dr Yassmin can assess your recovery and ensure your implants and gums are healing properly.</p>\r\n<p>Once your implants have successfully bonded to your jaw bone, your interim prosthesis is replaced by your permanent new prosthetic teeth, restoring your smile and your confidence.</p>\r\n<p>After receiving your dental implants, it is essential you follow a thorough at-home brushing and flossing routine to keep your gums healthy so they can support your new teeth. You should also schedule regular appointment checkups every six months with Dr Yassmin to ensure your implants remain strong.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									', 'The Recovery Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '196-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 06:10:49', '2015-09-04 06:10:49', '', 196, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/196-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(704, 1, '2015-09-04 06:17:02', '2015-09-04 06:17:02', '<div class="text"><h2>CREATING PERFECT SMILES ONE TOOTH AT A TIME &ndash; All-On-4&trade;</h2>\n<p>For many years dentures have been the preferred solution for the replacement of missing teeth. However, although dentures are still popular, dental implants are quickly becoming one of the most sought after tooth replacement options today. And for many good reasons.</p>\n<p>Bringing dentures and dental implants together, All-On-4 implant retained dentures, enables patients to have a set of upper or lower dentures permanently secured, sometimes with as few as four dental implants.</p>\n<p>To learn more about All-on-4 and find out if youâ€™re an ideal candidate, schedule a consultation appointment with Dr Yassmin who will explain the procedure in non-medical terms and gladly answer your questions.</p>\n</div>', 'Case Studies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '198-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 06:17:02', '2015-09-04 06:17:02', '', 198, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/198-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
