(739, 1, '2015-09-07 01:26:53', '2015-09-07 01:26:53', '\r\n\r\n									<h2>GETTING&nbsp;A&nbsp;GOOD&nbsp;NIGHTâ€™S&nbsp;SLEEP</h2>\r\n<h2>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA &ndash; RISK FACTORS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>What are the risk factors that lead to this serious sleep disorder?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Excess weight.</strong> Obesity is one of the most common causes of sleep apnoea. The fat deposits accumulated around the upper airway tend to obstruct the breathing of the overweight person. A loss of around 5kg to 10kg may be enough to dramatically reduce the severity of the disorder.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Neck circumference and facial bone shape.</strong> People with a thicker neck may have a narrower airway. Facial bone shape &ndash; such as an undershot jaw &ndash; may also contribute to the development of OSA.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Enlarged tonsils.</strong> If your tonsils or adenoids become enlarged, your airway may also be blocked.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Use of alcohol, sedatives or tranquilisers.</strong> These substances relax the muscles in your throat. Alcohol, especially in the evening hampers the brainâ€™s reaction to sleep disordered breathing.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Smoking.</strong> Smokers are three times more likely to have obstructive Sleep Apnoea than are people whoâ€™ve never smoked. Smoking may increase the amount of inflammation and fluid retention in the upper airway.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Nasal congestion.</strong> If you have difficulty breathing through your nose &mdash; whether itâ€™s from an anatomical problem or allergies &mdash; youâ€™re more likely to develop obstructive sleep apnoea.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Gender.</strong> Men are twice as likely to have sleep apnoea. However, women increase their risk if theyâ€™re overweight, and their risk also appears to rise after menopause.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Age.</strong> Sleep apnoea occurs significantly more often in adults older than 60.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Family history.</strong> If you have family members with sleep apnoea, you may be at increased risk.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Medications,</strong> such as sleeping tablets and sedatives.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n				', 'Why Treat Sleep Apnoea', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '243-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-07 01:26:53', '2015-09-07 01:26:53', '', 243, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/243-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(740, 1, '2015-09-07 01:28:18', '2015-09-07 01:28:18', '\r\n\r\n									<h2>GETTING A GOOD NIGHTâ€™S SLEEP</h2>\r\n<h2>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA &ndash; SYMPTOMS</h2>\r\n<p>Obstructive Sleep Apnoea is not to be taken lightly.</p>\r\n<p>People with severe Sleep Apnoea have an increased risk of motor vehicle accidents and high blood pressure, and may have an increased risk of heart attack and stroke.</p>\r\n<p>Itâ€™s important to keep an eye for some of the symptoms that are characteristic of this serious sleeping disorder, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Loud, frequent snoring,</li>\r\n<li>Poor daytime concentration,</li>\r\n<li>Irritability and mood changes</li>\r\n<li>Daytime sleepiness, fatigue and tiredness,</li>\r\n<li>Impotence and reduced sex drive,</li>\r\n<li>Need to frequently go to the toilet at night,</li>\r\n<li>Episodes of gasping, snorting or choking during sleep,</li>\r\n<li>Lack of energy and endurance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Keeping a sleep diary will help you understand your patterns and discover potential symptoms.Ask your sleep partner to keep track of your snoring, including volume and frequency &ndash; taking a video or audio recording is a good idea, and any gasping, choking, or other unusual sounds.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n		', 'Symptoms', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '246-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-07 01:28:18', '2015-09-07 01:28:18', '', 246, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/246-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(741, 1, '2015-09-07 01:29:26', '2015-09-07 01:29:26', '\r\n\r\n									<h2>GETTING A GOOD NIGHTâ€™S SLEEP</h2>\r\n<h2>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA &ndash; PROCESS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Do you feel lethargic at work? Irritable? Lacking in energy?</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you experience any of the symptoms generally associated with Obstructive Sleep Apnoea, donâ€™t take them lightly. Sleep Apnoea is a serious condition that can be easily diagnosed and should be treated by a certified physician.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Diagnosing Sleep Apnoea</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prior to diagnosing the condition, the physician will need to know your symptoms, as well as any circumstances and significant changes in your life that might be contributing to it &ndash; including, whether you have recently put on weight or stopped exercising.</p>\r\n<p>Sleep Apnoea can be diagnosed using an in-lab sleep study or a home sleep test.</p>\r\n<p>You may also need to keep a sleep diary for two weeks describing your sleep patterns, including what time you went to bed each night, when you woke up in the morning and how many times you woke up each night.</p>\r\n<p>Polysomnographic testing &ndash; whether conducted in a lab or at home &ndash; is used to help the sleep physician evaluate your problem. While there are other types of screenings that claim to detect sleep apnoea accurately, none is as reliable as polysomnographic testing. Beware of any commercial apps or other devices not recommended by a qualified physician.</p>\r\n<p>If you are diagnosed with sleep apnoea, your doctor will discuss your treatment options with you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Treating Sleep Apnoea</strong></p>\r\n<p>Treating sleep apnoea starts with changes to your lifestyle, including losing weight and cutting down on alcohol and quitting smoking. Any other contributing medical or surgical conditions such as low production of thyroid hormone and large tonsils should be corrected.</p>\r\n<p>Two treatments are generally used to treat OSA:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Nasal continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br>\r\nA device that pumps air under pressure into the airway, keeping the windpipe open during sleep. Unfortunately, a significant number of people with sleep apnoea find the mask difficult to tolerate.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mandibular Advancement Splints (Mouthguards)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br>\r\nMandibular repositioning appliances reposition and maintain the lower jaw in a forward position during sleep. This opens the upper airway and repositions the lower jaw and tongue in a more forward position away from the throat.</p>\r\n<p>Dental Splints are comfortable and easy to wear and most people find that it only takes a couple of weeks to become acclimatised to wearing them.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n	', 'Treatment Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '248-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-07 01:29:26', '2015-09-07 01:29:26', '', 248, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/248-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(742, 1, '2015-09-07 01:30:43', '2015-09-07 01:30:43', '\r\n\r\n									<h2>GETTING A GOOD NIGHTâ€™S SLEEP</h2>\r\n<h2>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA &ndash; BEDTIME TIPS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Tired of being elbowed by your partner every night?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put an end to your snoring sessions today &ndash; whether you do it for them or whether you do it for you, the important thing is to do it now!</p>\r\n<p>Get your physician to study your sleep patterns and seek appropriate treatment if you are diagnosed with Obstructive Sleep Disorder.</p>\r\n<p>However, before you talk to Dr Yassmin about potentially having a Dental Splint fitted to your mouth to treat Sleep Apnoea, there are a few things you can do to minimise your snoring:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Raise your head up while sleeping.</strong> Elevate your body from the waist up by using a foam wedge or the head of your bed by four to six inches. Cervical pillows are also recommended.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sleep on your side.</strong> Avoid sleeping on your back, as your tongue and soft tissues are more likely to drop and obstruct your airway. To keep yourself from rolling onto your back while you sleep, some suggest sewing a tennis ball into a pocket on the back of your pyjama top. Others go as far as recommending wedging a pillow stuffed with tennis balls behind your back.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Open your nasal passages.</strong> Try using a saline spray, nasal dilator or breathing strips regularly.</li>\r\n<li>Throat exercises to reduce sleep apnoea. Throat exercises may reduce the severity of Sleep Apnoea by strengthening the muscles in the airway, making them less likely to collapse. Here are some exercises you can practice regularly:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press your tongue on the roof of your mouth and hold it there three minutes a day.</li>\r\n<li>Press your tongue flat against the floor of your mouth and brush sides and top with a toothbrush. Repeat brushing movement five times, three times a day.</li>\r\n<li>Purse your lips in a kiss-like movement. Hold your lips tightly together and move them up and to the right, then up and to the left 10 times. Repeat this exercise three times.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n									\r\n			', 'Bed Time Tips', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '250-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-07 01:30:43', '2015-09-07 01:30:43', '', 250, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/250-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
