(758, 1, '2015-09-10 06:52:10', '2015-09-10 06:52:10', '<strong>DENTAL CROWNS: RESTORING YOUR TEETH AND ORAL HEALTH</strong>\r\nDental crowns (or caps) are designed to cover or ''cap'' a tooth to restore it to its normal shape and size, strengthening and improving its appearance.\r\n\r\n<strong>When are Dental Crowns used?</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen a tooth has broken down to the extent that fillings will no longer solve the problem,\r\n\r\nï‚·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  For heavily restored teeth that are vulnerable to fracture,\r\n\r\nï‚·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  In the case of cracked, broken, badly shaped or discoloured teeth, or\r\n\r\nï‚·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  In teeth that have undergone root canal therapy.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are dental crowns made of?</strong>\r\n\r\nThey can be made from a variety of materials including porcelain, metal or both.\r\nPorcelain dental crowns tend to be preferred because they are extremely strong while mimicking the translucency of natural tooth enamel.\r\n\r\nDr Yassmin''s team at Broadway Dental will custom-make your Dental Crown to fit perfectly well over your prepared tooth structure.', 'Dental Crowns', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '212-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-10 06:52:10', '2015-09-10 06:52:10', '', 212, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/212-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
