(764, 1, '2015-09-10 08:11:25', '2015-09-10 08:11:25', '<strong>WHITE FILLINGS</strong>\n\n<strong>KEEPING YOUR SMILE LOOKING NATURALLY BEAUTIFUL</strong>\n\n<strong>What are White Fillings?</strong>\n\nWhite Fillings have become the preferred option for the treatment of cavities today.\n\nThey can also be used to replace unsightly grey amalgam or gold restorations.\n\nWhat are the advantages of white fillings?\n<ul>\n	<li>White fillings offer a more natural tooth-like appearance,</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>By nature of their chemical composition, white fillings allow a more conservative approach to the restoration of decayed teeth.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>With white fillings, there is no need to remove healthy tooth structure as would be the case with the old style treatments.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>White fillings are a much improved alternative to earlier large long-term mercury fillings which, expanded and contracted with heat and cold causing the surrounding tooth structure to fracture.</li>\n</ul>\nHow are White Fillings fitted?\n\nInitially, a special dye is used to determine the extent of the decay. After that, it is safely removed and a whole filling bonded to the affected area.\n\nDepending on the size and extent of the decay, there are two White Fillings treatment options:\n<ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>Composite Resin Filling - A direct procedure that can be completed in a single visit by moulding a pliable material to the shape of the tooth and hardening it with a special blue light.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>Indirect Porcelain Restoration - Suitable for larger broken down teeth. Also known as Inlays or Onlays, these types of fillings are precision-manufactured in a laboratory from a mould of the tooth using high grade porcelains, selected for its strength, durability and natural appearance.</li>\n</ul>', 'White Fillings', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-10 08:11:25', '2015-09-10 08:11:25', '', 166, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/166-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(765, 1, '2015-09-10 08:10:23', '2015-09-10 08:10:23', 'WHITE FILLINGS\r\n\r\nKEEPING YOUR SMILE LOOKING NATURALLY BEAUTIFUL\r\n\r\nWhat are White Fillings?\r\n\r\nWhite Fillings have become the preferred option for the treatment of cavities today.\r\n\r\nThey can also be used to replace unsightly grey amalgam or gold restorations.\r\n\r\nWhat are the advantages of white fillings?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>White fillings offer a more natural tooth-like appearance,</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>By nature of their chemical composition, white fillings allow a more conservative approach to the restoration of decayed teeth.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With white fillings, there is no need to remove healthy tooth structure as would be the case with the old style treatments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>White fillings are a much improved alternative to earlier large long-term mercury fillings which, expanded and contracted with heat and cold causing the surrounding tooth structure to fracture.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHow are White Fillings fitted?\r\n\r\nInitially, a special dye is used to determine the extent of the decay. After that, it is safely removed and a whole filling bonded to the affected area.\r\n\r\nDepending on the size and extent of the decay, there are two White Fillings treatment options:\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Composite Resin Filling - A direct procedure that can be completed in a single visit by moulding a pliable material to the shape of the tooth and hardening it with a special blue light.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Indirect Porcelain Restoration - Suitable for larger broken down teeth. Also known as Inlays or Onlays, these types of fillings are precision-manufactured in a laboratory from a mould of the tooth using high grade porcelains, selected for its strength, durability and natural appearance.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'White Fillings', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-10 08:10:23', '2015-09-10 08:10:23', '', 166, 'http:/