(778, 1, '2015-09-10 08:35:06', '2015-09-10 08:35:06', '<div class="text">\r\n									<div itemtype="http://schema.org/VideoObject" itemscope="" itemprop="video">\r\n<h2><span itemprop="name">THE CLEAR WAY TO A PERFECTLY STRAIGHT SMILE &ndash; INVISALIGN</span></h2>\r\n<p><meta content="T02M16S" itemprop="duration"><meta content="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/8XH0-kzg8jw/hqdefault.jpg" itemprop="thumbnailUrl"><meta content="https://www.youtube.com/v/8XH0-kzg8jw" itemprop="contentURL"><meta content="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8XH0-kzg8jw" itemprop="embedURL"><br>\r\n<iframe width="390" height="219" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8XH0-kzg8jw?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;controls=1&amp;autohide=1"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong><span itemprop="description">To find our more about Invisalign (invisable braces) book an appointment with Dr. Fadi Yassmin at Broadway Dental today!</span> </strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>The smile youâ€™ve always dreamed of with Invisalign</h2>\r\n<p>Have you been hiding your smile because you fear othersâ€™ negative reactions? Are you not confident about the way your teeth look?</p>\r\n<p>If youâ€™d like a straighter, more beautiful smile without going through traditional orthodontic treatments, Invisalign may be the answer for you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is Invisalign?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Invisalign is a revolutionary cosmetic dental treatment that uses a series of removable clear aligners (or invisible braces) to gradually straighten your teeth.</p>\r\n<p>It is a far more comfortable and a lot less intrusive method than traditional orthodontic treatments.</p>\r\n<p>With Invisalign, you can achieve the smile of your dreams without anyone noticing youâ€™re undergoing a dental treatment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are the benefits of Invisalign?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Invisalign is ideal for those who have always wanted a better smile but have been putting off orthodontic treatments because of the social stigma associated with braces.</li>\r\n<li>The durable, transparent thermoplastic material of the Invisalign aligners make them almost impossible to see and as such, a much more discreet alternative to orthodontic treatments.</li>\r\n<li>Being completely removable, it is easy to maintain the daily oral hygiene routine needed to reduce the chance of plaque build-up, tooth decay and gum disease.</li>\r\n<li>These invisible braces donâ€™t rely on traditional metal appliances, so food and plaque are not trapped on the surface of the teeth.</li>\r\n<li>It is a surprisingly fast treatment, with most of our patients requiring approximately less than a year to transform their smile and be able to display their beautiful new look.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>YOUR INVISALIGN TREATMENT</h2>\r\n<p>During your initial consultation at Broadway Dentalâ€™s Sydney Clinic, Dr Yassmin will gain an understanding of your current situation, and explore your goals to determine if Invisalign is suitable for you.</p>\r\n<p>Should this be the case, Dr Yassmin will then begin by taking detailed impressions of your teeth. These will then be digitised to create a computerised 3D image of your smile from which, Dr Yassmin will be able to determine the precise movements needed to create the best results.</p>\r\n<p>Subsequently, your custom-made invisible braces will be crafted according to your individual treatment plan.<br>\r\nThe number of aligners you will need will depend on your needs and goals however, a full Invisalign treatment typically involves the use of 18 to 36 aligners, and it takes around 9 to 18 months.</p>\r\n<h2>LIVING WITH INVISALIGN</h2>\r\n<p>During your treatment, you will wear each aligner for around two weeks, day and night, with small breaks for eating, brushing and flossing your teeth, and the occasional time off for special events. After two weeks, you will then switch to the next aligner which, will move your teeth a little more.</p>\r\n<p>We will ask you to come in for a check-up every 4-6 weeks so that we can monitor your progress and provide you with your next set of aligners.</p>\r\n<p>Throughout your treatment, you should notice small movements as the invisible braces gradually move your teeth to create an even, healthy and very attractive smile.</p>\r\n<p>To find out how Invisalign can help you achieve a Hollywood smile, call us today on <span class="AVANSERnumber">(02) 9281 0100</span> or via email.</p>\r\n<h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>How does Invisalign work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The aligners in the Invisalign apply consistent, controlled force to individual teeth, gently moving them into their new desired position.</p>\r\n<p>Invisalign differs from traditional braces in that it actually controls the amount of force applied to each tooth and this reduces the length of the treatment in comparison with traditional orthodontics.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How effective is Invisalign?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Studies show that out of the 1.5 million people who have had or are having Invisalign treatment, 98% of them are satisfied with the results.</p>\r\n<p>However, itâ€™s important to remember that Invisalign cannot treat all orthodontic conditions such as severe over or underbites, severely tipped teeth, numerous missing teeth, or unerupted teeth.</p>\r\n<p>To find out whether Invisalign is right for you, talk to the team at Broadway Dental on <span class="AVANSERnumber">(02) 9281 0100</span> or via email.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does Invisalign look like?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The clear, strong, non-toxic plastic material Invisalign aligners are manufactured with, make them very difficult to see when worn. Besides, having been custom-made specifically for each patient according to their treatment plan, aligners fit very neatly to the teeth.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How long does Invisalign treatment take?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Treatment times vary but on average, patients achieve straighter teeth with Invisalign in around twelve to fourteen months, four months less than traditional braces.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Is Invisalign painful?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Wearing the Invisalign aligners is generally far more comfortable than wearing traditional braces. Minor discomfort may be experienced initially and for a few days every time a new aligner is used. This slight feeling of pressure is a sign aligners are doing their job and moving the teeth into the desired position. Any discomfort is usually relieved in a few days.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How much does Invisalign cost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The cost of an Invisalign treatment depends on individual circumstances but for most of our patients at Broadway Dental, the cost of a full treatment ranges between $5,000 and $10,000.</p>\r\n<p>After our initial consultation weâ€™ll be able to provide you with a treatment plan detailing all costs for your specific needs.</p>\r\n																			<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your free consultation</a>\r\n																												<a title="Invisalign Sydney Cases" class="book-now" href="http://broadwaydental.com.au/gallery/invisalign/">See Our Invisalign Success Stories</a>\r\n																	</div>', 'Invisalign', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-10 08:35:06', '2015-09-10 08:35:06', '', 95, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
