(953, 1, '2015-09-11 07:36:21', '2015-09-11 07:36:21', '&lt;h2&gt;WHAT IS ALL ON 4 DENTAL IMPLANT&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;What is All On 4 dental implant?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The All-On-4 system offered at Broadway Dental represents the state of the art in implant dentistry, which brings a dental prosthesis and dental implants together.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A dental implant is a fine titanium screw or rod placed into the jaw bone during a minor surgical procedure to replace a missing tooth root. Titanium is a strong bio-compatible alloy and has been used successfully in reconstructive medicine for many years as it naturally integrates with bone.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Previously, a single dental implant was placed vertically and used to replace a single tooth or support a dental bridge of up to three teeth. To support an entire upper or lower arch of teeth, up to eight dental implants were necessary.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The All-On-4 System enables you to have a set of upper or lower prosthetic teeth permanently secured, often with as few as four dental implants.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The treatment is made possible because two of the implants are slightly longer than traditional dental implants. They are also placed at an acute angle at the front of the mouth where your jaw bone is denser and stronger, and provides the greatest support for your prosthesis.&lt;/p&gt;', 'All on 4 Procedure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '137-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 07:36:21', '2015-09-11 07:36:21', '', 137, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/137-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
