(957, 1, '2015-09-11 08:21:49', '2015-09-11 08:21:49', '<h2>WHAT IS ALL ON 4 DENTAL IMPLANT</h2>\r\nWhat is All On 4 dental implant?\r\n\r\nThe All-On-4 system offered at Broadway Dental represents the state of the art in implant dentistry, which brings a dental prosthesis and dental implants together.\r\n\r\nA dental implant is a fine titanium screw or rod placed into the jaw bone during a minor surgical procedure to replace a missing tooth root. Titanium is a strong bio-compatible alloy and has been used successfully in reconstructive medicine for many years as it naturally integrates with bone.\r\nPreviously, a single dental implant was placed vertically and used to replace a single tooth or support a dental bridge of up to three teeth. To support an entire upper or lower arch of teeth, up to eight dental implants were necessary.\r\nThe All-On-4 System enables you to have a set of upper or lower prosthetic teeth permanently secured, often with as few as four dental implants.\r\nThe treatment is made possible because two of the implants are slightly longer than traditional dental implants. They are also placed at an acute angle at the front of the mouth where your jaw bone is denser and stronger, and provides the greatest support for your prosthesis.', 'All on 4 Procedure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '137-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 08:21:49', '2015-09-11 08:21:49', '', 137, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/137-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(958, 1, '2015-09-11 08:25:15', '2015-09-11 08:25:15', '<h2>PREPARING FOR YOUR PROCEDURE</h2>\r\nÂ \r\nWhat is pre-operative care in All On Four procedure? This is the most important phase of your treatment. Ensuring you are in good oral health can help reduce recovery time and aid in long-term success.\r\nÂ \r\nDr Yassmin will take the time to explain the procedure in detail, develop a tailored treatment plan and answer all of your questions.\r\nÂ \r\nThe first step is to have a comprehensive examination of your oral health to determine your suitability. General health conditions such as diabetes, oral health conditions such as gum disease and lifestyle decisions such as smoking can all cause complications and affect the success of the procedure.\r\nÂ \r\nYour tooth roots are responsible for keeping your jaw bone strong and healthy. If you have been missing teeth for some time, it''s possible to have lost some bone density and volume.\r\nÂ \r\nA 3-D CT (CAT) scan is taken and produces a highly detailed image of your bone structure. This is used to evaluate your bone quality and density. Then advanced computer imaging software is used to plan your surgery and ensure precise placement of your implants.\r\nÂ \r\nThe final stage involves creating detailed impression moulds of your gum line and taking photographs. These will ensure your new smile looks natural and your new prosthetic teeth bite together perfectly.\r\nÂ \r\nOur goal is to keep you safe, and we take that responsibility very seriously. That is why we collect a full medical history from each of our patients and perform specific medical tests prior to the procedure. These medical tests include bloods and an ECG, and they are performed prior to the procedure to ensure that you stay safe from start to finish.', 'Pre - Operative Care', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '192-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 08:25:15', '2015-09-11 08:25:15', '', 192, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/192-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(959, 1, '2015-09-11 08:26:07', '2015-09-11 08:26:07', '<h2>PREPARING FOR YOUR PROCEDURE</h2>\r\nWhat is pre-operative care in All On Four procedure? This is the most important phase of your treatment. Ensuring you are in good oral health can help reduce recovery time and aid in long-term success.\r\n\r\nDr Yassmin will take the time to explain the procedure in detail, develop a tailored treatment plan and answer all of your questions.\r\n\r\nThe first step is to have a comprehensive examination of your oral health to determine your suitability. General health conditions such as diabetes, oral health conditions such as gum disease and lifestyle decisions such as smoking can all cause complications and affect the success of the procedure.\r\n\r\nYour tooth roots are responsible for keeping your jaw bone strong and healthy. If you have been missing teeth for some time, it''s possible to have lost some bone density and volume.\r\n\r\nA 3-D CT (CAT) scan is taken and produces a highly detailed image of your bone structure. This is used to evaluate your bone quality and density. Then advanced computer imaging software is used to plan your surgery and ensure precise placement of your implants.\r\n\r\nThe final stage involves creating detailed impression moulds of your gum line and taking photographs. These will ensure your new smile looks natural and your new prosthetic teeth bite together perfectly.\r\n\r\nOur goal is to keep you safe, and we take that responsibility very seriously. That is why we collect a full medical history from each of our patients and perform specific medical tests prior to the procedure. These medical tests include bloods and an ECG, and they are performed prior to the procedure to ensure that you stay safe from start to finish.', 'Pre - Operative Care', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '192-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 08:26:07', '2015-09-11 08:26:07', '', 192, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/192-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '',