(960, 1, '2015-09-11 08:35:00', '2015-09-11 08:35:00', '<h2>ALL ON 4 FAQS</h2>\r\n<div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingOne">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">\r\n          Q: Is implant surgery painful?\r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n        A. With various anaesthetic options available your procedure can be completed quickly and with little to no discomfort. We can also provide IV Sedation, sometimes called Sleep Dentistry, which is completely safe and where you are in a deeply relaxed state.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingTwo">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">\r\n          Q. What''s the difference between the All-On-4 System and MDI?\r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingTwo">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n        A. With the All-On-4 System, the four dental implants are placed strategically at the front and back of your mouth. This provides maximum stability and allows the dentist to securely install the fixed bridge. \r\nThese MDI (Mini Dental Implants) are a much finer implant and have a ball head with a rubber O-ring. This allows a prosthesis to lock into place and also be removed. Mini Dental Implants are also shorter and placed vertically Just as importantly, MDI do not integrate into the bone. This means the MDI is a temporary solution - one that can only be used with overdenture systems.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingThree">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">\r\n          Q. Why replace missing teeth?\r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingThree">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n        A. When you have missing teeth, whether it''s one or an entire arch, it can have a detrimental effect on your oral and general health. If you have teeth on either side of a gap they can move out of alignment and into the space, making them harder to clean and increasing the risk of gum disease. Missing teeth can also result in your jaw bone losing density and volume.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n<div class="panel panel-default">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingTwo">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">\r\n          Q. How successful is the All-On-4 System?\r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFour">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n        A. The All-On-4 System offered at Broadway Dental enjoys a very high success rate with published statistics showing a greater than 98 per cent on the lower arch and 94 percent on the upper arch. The high success rate is attributed to how the implants are placed, bone density and on-going oral hygiene appointments every six months to ensure optimal gum and oral health is achieved and maintained.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>', 'FAQ''s', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '182-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 08:35:00', '2015-09-11 08:35:00', '', 182, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/182-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(961, 1, '2015-09-11 08:41:31', '2015-09-11 08:41:31', '<h2>All-On-4â„¢</h2>\n<h2>ALL ON FOUR DENTAL IMPLANTS EXPLAINED:</h2>\nÂ \nLiving with the stigma that comes with missing teeth? Too embarrassed to be seen in public without your full smile?\nÂ \nFor many years dentures have been the preferred solution for the replacement of missing teeth:\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Complete dentures are used by people who have lost all their natural upper or lower teeth.</li>\n\n\n	<li>Partial dentures are for patients who still retain some of their natural teeth.</li>\n\n\n	<li>Severely damaged teeth</li>\n\n\n	<li>Advanced periodontal disease</li>\n\n</ul>\n\n\nÂ \n\nAlthough dentures are still popular, Dental Implants are quickly becoming one of the most sought after tooth replacement options today. Replicating a missing tooth root, Dental Implants are fine titanium screws or rods that are placed into the jawbone.\nÂ \nThe latest innovation in modern dentistry- All-on-4\nÂ \nBringing dentures and dental implants together, All-On-4 Implant Retained Dentures, enable patients to have a set of upper or lower dentures permanently secured, sometimes with as few as four Dental Implants.\nÂ \nHow is this achieved?\nÂ \nSimply by placing two of the four implants at an angle at the front of the mouth where the jawbone is denser and stronger.\nÂ \nHow do I maintain my All-on-4 Implant Retained Dentures?\nÂ \nAfter receiving your All-on-4 Implant Retained Dentures, it is essential you follow a thorough at-home brushing and flossing routine. You should also schedule regular appointment check-ups every six months with Dr Yassmin to ensure your implants remain strong.\nÂ \nTo learn more about All-on-4 and find out if you''re an ideal candidate to use them, schedule a consultation appointment with Dr Yassmin who will explain the procedure in non-medical terms and gladly answer any of your questions.\nÂ \nPlease note: Any surgical or invasive procedure carries risks. Before proceeding, you should seek a second opinion from an appropriately qualified health practitioner.', 'All on 4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 08:41:31', '2015-09-11 08:41:31', '', 14, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/14-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
