(1085, 1, '2015-09-14 07:29:47', '2015-09-14 07:29:47', '<div class="inn_contant">	\r\n<h3>ALL-ON-4 RECOVERY PROCESS</h3>\r\nÂ \r\nEveryone is different and your complete recovery will depend on your oral and general health. Most people are able to return to work and their normal daily routine the following day, however, the average time for implants to integrate fully with your jaw bone is four to six months.\r\nÂ \r\nBiting and chewing places extreme pressure on your teeth and gums. It is advised to have a soft food diet for at least two months after receiving your implants. If you experience any discomfort it can be relieved with a cold compress and over-the-counter medication.\r\nÂ \r\nYou may also be required to visit our clinic one week, four weeks and 12 weeks after your procedure so Dr Yassmin can assess your recovery and ensure your implants and gums are healing properly.\r\nÂ \r\nOnce your implants have successfully bonded in 24 hrs to your jaw bone, your permanent new prosthetic teeth will restore your smile and your confidence.\r\n\r\nAfter receiving your dental implants, it is essential you follow a thorough at-home brushing and flossing routine to keep your gums healthy so they can support your new teeth. You should also schedule regular appointment checkups every six months with Dr Yassmin to ensure your implants remain strong.\r\n</div>', 'The Recovery Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '196-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:29:47', '2015-09-14 07:29:47', '', 196, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/196-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1086, 1, '2015-09-14 07:29:59', '2015-09-14 07:29:59', '<div class="inn_contant">	\r\n<h3>ALL-ON-4 RECOVERY PROCESS</h3>\r\nÂ Everyone is different and your complete recovery will depend on your oral and general health. Most people are able to return to work and their normal daily routine the following day, however, the average time for implants to integrate fully with your jaw bone is four to six months.\r\nÂ \r\nBiting and chewing places extreme pressure on your teeth and gums. It is advised to have a soft food diet for at least two months after receiving your implants. If you experience any discomfort it can be relieved with a cold compress and over-the-counter medication.\r\nÂ \r\nYou may also be required to visit our clinic one week, four weeks and 12 weeks after your procedure so Dr Yassmin can assess your recovery and ensure your implants and gums are healing properly.\r\nÂ \r\nOnce your implants have successfully bonded in 24 hrs to your jaw bone, your permanent new prosthetic teeth will restore your smile and your confidence.\r\n\r\nAfter receiving your dental implants, it is essential you follow a thorough at-home brushing and flossing routine to keep your gums healthy so they can support your new teeth. You should also schedule regular appointment checkups every six months with Dr Yassmin to ensure your implants remain strong.\r\n</div>', 'The Recovery Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '196-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:29:59', '2015-09-14 07:29:59', '', 196, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/196-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1087, 1, '2015-09-14 07:32:15', '2015-09-14 07:32:15', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n \r\n[su_accordion]\r\n      [su_spoiler title="Q. Is implant surgery painful?" style="fancy"] A. With various anaesthetic options available your procedure can be completed quickly and with little to no discomfort. We can also provide IV Sedation, sometimes called Sleep Dentistry, which is completely safe and where you are in a deeply relaxed state.  [/su_spoiler]\r\n  [su_spoiler title="Q. What''s the difference between the All-On-4 System and MDI?" style="fancy"] A. With the All-On-4 System, the four dental implants are placed strategically at the front and back of your mouth. This provides maximum stability and allows the dentist to securely install the fixed bridge. \r\nThese MDI (Mini Dental Implants) are a much finer implant and have a ball head with a rubber O-ring. This allows a prosthesis to lock into place and also be removed. Mini Dental Implants are also shorter and placed vertically Just as importantly, MDI do not integrate into the bone. This means the MDI is a temporary solution - one that can only be used with overdenture systems. Spoiler content [/su_spoiler]\r\n[su_spoiler title="Q. Why replace missing teeth?" style="fancy"] A. When you have missing teeth, whether it''s one or an entire arch, it can have a detrimental effect on your oral and general health. If you have teeth on either side of a gap they can move out of alignment and into the space, making them harder to clean and increasing the risk of gum disease. Missing teeth can also result in your jaw bone losing density and volume. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[su_spoiler title="Q. How successful is the All-On-4 System?" style="fancy"] A. The All-On-4 System offered at Broadway Dental enjoys a very high success rate with published statistics showing a greater than 98 per cent on the lower arch and 94 percent on the upper arch. The high success rate is attributed to how the implants are placed, bone density and on-going oral hygiene appointments every six months to ensure optimal gum and oral health is achieved and maintained. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[/su_accordion]\r\n</div>', 'FAQ''s', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '182-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:32:15', '2015-09-14 07:32:15', '', 182, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/182-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1088, 1, '2015-09-14 07:33:07', '2015-09-14 07:33:07', '<div class="treatments">\n								<h2>Treatment provided</h2>\n								<div class="treatments-provided">\n									<ul>\n<li>Photos and Radiographic records</li>\n<li>Photos and radiographic records were taken to allow accurate assessment of the existing dentition (development and arrangement of teeth in his mouth) and to give Donald a visual view of the treatment needed.</li>\n<li>Preventative care (Dental prophylaxis)</li>\n<li>Deep scaling and polishing to remove the buildup of heavy plaque (also known as calculus and tartar) and staining on Donald''s teeth, helping prevent cavities and gum disease</li>\n<li>Oral hygiene routine - Cariscreen and caries free rinse program. Custom trays of GC tooth mousse were created for home use, which will help prevent tooth decay (that can lead to cavities, pain, tooth loss and infection) and minimise intrinsic staining (white specs on teeth).</li>\n<li>Extractions -Removal of highly infected teeth was performed to enable a healthy mouth.</li>\n<li>Upper and lower partial denture - Due to the tight time frame an upper and lower partial denture was made. Valplast dentures were made for a highly aesthetic and functional result.</li>\n<li>Teeth whitening - BriteSmile whitening system was used to whiten Donald''s teeth. Custom trays were also made to give Donald a whitening maintenance program to take home to help sustain his whiter smile.</li>\n</ul>									<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\n<div class="clear"></div>\n								</div>\n								</div>', 'EPISODE 1 ANETTE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '751-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:33:07', '2015-09-14 07:33:07', '', 751, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/751-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1089, 1, '2015-09-14 07:48:22', '2015-09-14 07:48:22', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\nWhen you need dental services, you need to know the dentist is someone you can trust. You need to know your dental professional has the training, the experience and the expertise necessary to take care of your smile, keep you safe and make sure you are satisfied with your new smile.\r\n\r\nDr. Fadi Yassmin is one of the most widely respected dentists in the industry, with a Master''s Degree in Aesthetic Dentistry and ongoing training from such prestigious institutions as the renowned Kings College, the Australian Academy of Dento-Facial Aesthetics and UCLA - widely regarded as one of the world''s leading medical centreâ€™s.\r\n\r\nSince 1998, Dr. Fadi Yassmin has been leading the impressive team at the Broadway Dental Centre in Sydney Ultimo. During nearly two decades of practice with the Broadway Dental Centre, Dr. Yassmin has developed a reputation as one of the leading dental practitioners in the city.\r\n\r\nSince the very beginning, Dr. Fadi Yassmin and his team have been committed to serving the needs of their patients - and to providing top quality pain-free dental services. If you want to improve your smile and your life, you should give Dr. Yassmin a call.\r\n\r\nDr. Yassmin remains at the forefront of dentistry, and he has worked hard to make Broadway Dental Centre a warm, inviting and relaxing place to be. Even the most fearful patients will instantly relax as they discuss their oral healthcare needs with Dr. Yassmin and his staff.\r\n\r\nAmong the services Dr. Fadi Yassmin and his staff perform are:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cosmetic dentistry</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Smile makeovers</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Invisaligns</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Dental implants</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Teeth whitening</li>\r\n\r\n<li> Sleep dentistry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>A Philosophy of Caring</h4>\r\n\r\nFrom the very beginning, Dr. Fadi Yassmin and his staff have been passionate about improving the lives of his patients. The top quality general and cosmetic dentistry services they provide are all based on a very simple philosophy - listening to the concerns of each patient, understanding their specific needs and goals and communicating openly and honestly with everyone who comes through the doors of their clinic.\r\n\r\nDr. Yassmin knows that quality dental care takes time. That is why he spends as much time as necessary discussing oral health and dental options with every patient he serves. At Broadway Dental, we do not believe in rushing patients - we are dedicated in making sure every patient understands the procedures that will transform their smiles and improve their lives.\r\nIn addition to taking time to get to know each patient, Dr Yassmin works hard to customise the best dental treatment for each of his patients. In order to do that, Dr. Yassmin stays at the forefront of modern dentistry and seeks the best continuing education in the industry. That is why Broadway Dental has made significant investments in cutting-edge dental technology and advanced training for all members of the team.\r\n\r\n<h4>His training</h4>\r\n\r\nSince graduating from Sydney University in 1993, Dr Yassmin has always felt passionate about excelling in his career. After founding Broadway Dental in 1998, he knew he had to stay informed about national and international developments in his field, and he has remained constantly up-to-date with the latest technological advancements so he can better serve his patients.\r\n\r\nThat is also why Dr Yassmin constantly invests in ongoing education and post graduate courses -- both in Australia and overseas, including his recent completion of a Masters in Aesthetic Dentistry. His revolutionary new facet of cosmetic dentistry goes beyond creating a traditional smile makeover. Using the most up-to-date cosmetic dental techniques, Dr Yassmin can now work in harmony with the facial structure of each patient, allowing him to create a beautiful smile while smoothing out the wrinkles and folds of the face.\r\n\r\nHis recent Master''s is just the latest in a long line of continuing education programs Dr. Yassmin has completed. In order to complete his Master''s in Aesthetic Dentistry , Dr. Yassmin attended the prestigious Kings College in London - widely regarded as one of the top institutions of its kind in the entire world.\r\n\r\n<h4>The result?</h4>\r\n\r\nAll this hard work, dedication and ongoing training has been undertaken with a single goal in mind - to help every patient obtain the look they have always wanted.\r\n\r\nThe end result of all this dental education is a much younger looking patient - a patient who feels happier, rejuvenated and a lot more confident.\r\n\r\n<h4>His exposure in the media</h4>\r\n\r\nDr Yassmin''s reputation as an authority in dento-facial aesthetics has been cemented through his work on the hit show "10 Years Younger in 10 Days", where he applied his broad experience and impressive skills to change the lives of patients in urgent need of a smile makeover.\r\n\r\nDr Yassmin has also shared his expert tips in Troy Thompson''s book "Guide to the Younger You". In addition to that extensive media exposure, Dr. Yassmin has also become a regular with many bloggers. Those bloggers recognize Dr. Yassmin for his expertise, and they appreciate the expert tips he provides to their readers.\r\n\r\n<h4>His team</h4>\r\n\r\nCarefully selected by Dr Fadi Yassmin, the members of the team at Broadway Dental reflect his philosophy of care and apply it every day to ensure their patients'' experience is one they will remember and will be happy to recommend to friends and family.\r\n\r\nDr Yassmin also provides regular training to ensure every single member of the team understands the treatments offered at Broadway Dental. The extensive communication Dr. Yassim and his team provide mean patients feel free to discuss their needs -- knowing that they are being understood and that they are always provided with appropriate care and informed advice.\r\n\r\nTo find out more about our services, call us on 02-92810100 or click here to book an appointment online.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Dr Fadi Yassmin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '103-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:48:22', '2015-09-14 07:48:22', '', 103, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/103-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
