erience much better oral health over the long term.</li>\r\n<li>Dental Implants can help you speak, chew and live normally once more, without having to ever worry about loose, ill-fitting dentures.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You wonâ€™t believe the feeling of self-confidence and comfort youâ€™ll experience, all thanks to Dental Implants!</p>\r\n<h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Are Dental Implants right for me?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dental Implants are a suitable treatment for most patients as long as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>They enjoy good oral and overall health,</li>\r\n<li>Have sufficient bone in the jaw to properly support an implant and,</li>\r\n<li>Do not suffer from gum disease.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Speak to the Broadway Dental team to arrange your personalised consultation and find out whether you are eligible to have Dental Implants by calling <span class="AVANSERnumber">(02) 9281 0100</span> or via email.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do dental implants look like?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Dental Implants themselves resemble tiny titanium screws which, are surgically implanted into your jaw bone. Once these titanium foundations have fully integrated with your bone, Dr Yassmin will place a natural-looking tooth coloured crown to fully restore the appearance and function of your tooth.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How long does a Dental Implant treatment take?</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you enjoy good oral health and you have sufficient jaw bone to work with, Dr Yassmin will be able to start on your dental implant treatment straight away. If you need bone grafting, this extra procedure will take around three months before your tooth implant placement can begin.</p>\r\n<p>In most cases, two appointments are all thatâ€™s needed to complete a full Dental Implant treatment. During your first appointment, the expert team of cosmetic dentists at Broadway Sydney will surgically place your implant. Three to six months later, at your second appointment, theyâ€™ll restore your tooth with a dental crown.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How will I look after my Dental Implants?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Just like your natural teeth, dental implants need a meticulous at-home oral hygiene routine and regular visits to our Sydney dental clinic for a long-lasting good health.</p>\r\n<p>You should continue to brush thoroughly twice a day, floss once a day, and attend twice-yearly check-ups with Dr Yassmin to ensure your overall oral health.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How long can I expect my Dental Implant to last?</strong></p>\r\n<p>With proper care and regular follow up appointments with Broadway Dental, dental implants can last a lifetime.</p>\r\n<p>Please note: Any surgical or invasive procedure carries a certain risk. Before proceeding, we advise you to seek a second opinion from an appropriately qualified oral health practitioner.</p>\r\n																			<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n																												<a title="Dental Implants Sydney Cases" class="book-now" href="http://broadwaydental.com.au/gallery/dental-implants/">our dental implants success stories</a>\r\n																										</div>', 'Dental Implants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '807-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:58:02', '2015-09-14 07:58:02', '', 807, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/807-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
