(1111, 1, '2015-09-14 08:35:32', '2015-09-14 08:35:32', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<h3>GETTING A GOOD NIGHT''S SLEEP</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA - PROCESS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Do you feel lethargic at work? Irritable? Lacking in energy?</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you experience any of the symptoms generally associated with Obstructive Sleep Apnoea, don''t take them lightly. Sleep Apnoea is a serious condition that can be easily diagnosed and should be treated by a certified physician.\r\n\r\n<h4>Diagnosing Sleep Apnoea</h4>\r\n\r\nPrior to diagnosing the condition, the physician will need to know your symptoms, as well as any circumstances and significant changes in your life that might be contributing to it - including, whether you have recently put on weight or stopped exercising.\r\n\r\n<h4>Sleep Apnoea can be diagnosed using an in-lab sleep study or a home sleep test.</h4>\r\n\r\nYou may also need to keep a sleep diary for two weeks describing your sleep patterns, including what time you went to bed each night, when you woke up in the morning and how many times you woke up each night.\r\n\r\nPolysomnographic testing - whether conducted in a lab or at home - is used to help the sleep physician evaluate your problem. While there are other types of screenings that claim to detect sleep apnoea accurately, none is as reliable as polysomnographic testing. Beware of any commercial apps or other devices not recommended by a qualified physician.\r\n\r\nIf you are diagnosed with sleep apnoea, your doctor will discuss your treatment options with you.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Treating Sleep Apnoea</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\nTreating sleep apnoea starts with changes to your lifestyle, including losing weight and cutting down on alcohol and quitting smoking. Any other contributing medical or surgical conditions such as low production of thyroid hormone and large tonsils should be corrected.\r\n\r\n<h4>Two treatments are generally used to treat OSA:</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Nasal continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP)</h4>\r\n\r\nA device that pumps air under pressure into the airway, keeping the windpipe open during sleep. Unfortunately, a significant number of people with sleep apnoea find the mask difficult to tolerate.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Mandibular Advancement Splints (Mouthguards)</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\nMandibular repositioning appliances reposition and maintain the lower jaw in a forward position during sleep. This opens the upper airway and repositions the lower jaw and tongue in a more forward position away from the throat.\r\n\r\nDental Splints are comfortable and easy to wear and most people find that it only takes a couple of weeks to become acclimatised to wearing them.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Sleep Apnoea Treatment Process', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'process', '', '', '2015-09-28 07:03:48', '2015-09-28 07:03:48', '', 240, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?page_id=1111', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(1112, 1, '2015-09-14 08:35:32', '2015-09-14 08:35:32', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<strong>SLEEP APNOEA TREATMENT PROCESS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>GETTING A GOOD NIGHT''S SLEEP</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA - PROCESS</strong>\r\n\r\n<h4>Do you feel lethargic at work? Irritable? Lacking in energy?</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you experience any of the symptoms generally associated with Obstructive Sleep Apnoea, don''t take them lightly. Sleep Apnoea is a serious condition that can be easily diagnosed and should be treated by a certified physician.\r\n\r\n<h4>Diagnosing Sleep Apnoea</h4>\r\n\r\nPrior to diagnosing the condition, the physician will need to know your symptoms, as well as any circumstances and significant changes in your life that might be contributing to it - including, whether you have recently put on weight or stopped exercising.\r\n\r\nSleep Apnoea can be diagnosed using an in-lab sleep study or a home sleep test.\r\n\r\nYou may also need to keep a sleep diary for two weeks describing your sleep patterns, including what time you went to bed each night, when you woke up in the morning and how many times you woke up each night.\r\n\r\nPolysomnographic testing - whether conducted in a lab or at home - is used to help the sleep physician evaluate your problem. While there are other types of screenings that claim to detect sleep apnoea accurately, none is as reliable as polysomnographic testing. Beware of any commercial apps or other devices not recommended by a qualified physician.\r\n\r\nIf you are diagnosed with sleep apnoea, your doctor will discuss your treatment options with you.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Treating Sleep Apnoea</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\nTreating sleep apnoea starts with changes to your lifestyle, including losing weight and cutting down on alcohol and quitting smoking. Any other contributing medical or surgical conditions such as low production of thyroid hormone and large tonsils should be corrected.\r\n\r\n<strong>Two treatments are generally used to treat OSA:</strong>\r\n\r\n<h4>Nasal continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP)</h4>\r\n\r\nA device that pumps air under pressure into the airway, keeping the windpipe open during sleep. Unfortunately, a significant number of people with sleep apnoea find the mask difficult to tolerate.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4> Mandibular Advancement Splints (Mouthguards)</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\nMandibular repositioning appliances reposition and maintain the lower jaw in a forward position during sleep. This opens the upper airway and repositions the lower jaw and tongue in a more forward position away from the throat.\r\n\r\nDental Splints are comfortable and easy to wear and most people find that it only takes a couple of weeks to become acclimatised to wearing them.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Sleep Apnoea Treatment Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1111-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 08:35:32', '2015-09-14 08:35:32', '', 1111, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/1111-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1113, 1, '2015-09-14 08:40:09', '2015-09-14 08:40:09', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<strong>BED TIME TIPS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>GETTING A GOOD NIGHT''S SLEEP</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA - BEDTIME TIPS</strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Tired of being elbowed by your partner every night?</h4>\r\n\r\nPut an end to your snoring sessions today - whether you do it for them or whether you do it for you, the important thing is to do it now!\r\n\r\nGet your physician to study your sleep patterns and seek appropriate treatment if you are diagnosed with Obstructive Sleep Disorder.\r\n\r\nHowever, before you talk to Dr Yassmin about potentially having a Dental Splint fitted to your mouth to treat Sleep Apnoea, there are a few things you can do to minimise your snoring:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Raise your head up while sleeping. Elevate your body from the waist up by using a foam wedge or the head of your bed by four to six inches. Cervical pillows are also recommended.</li>\r\n	<li>Sleep on your side. Avoid sleeping on your back, as your tongue and soft tissues are more likely to drop and obstruct your airway. To keep yourself from rolling onto your back while you sleep, some suggest sewing a tennis ball into a pocket on the back of your pyjama top. Others go as far as recommending wedging a pillow stuffed with tennis balls behind your back.</li>\r\n	<li>Open your nasal passages. Try using a saline spray, nasal dilator or breathing strips regularly.</li>\r\n	<li>Throat exercises to reduce sleep apnoea. Throat exercises may reduce the severity of Sleep Apnoea by strengthening the muscles in the airway, making them less likely to collapse. Here are some exercises you can practice regularly:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press your tongue on the roof of your mouth and hold it there three minutes a day.</li>\r\n\r\n<li> Press your tongue flat against the floor of your mouth and brush sides and top with a toothbrush. Repeat brushing movement five times, three times a day.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Purse your lips in a kiss-like movement. Hold your lips tightly together and move them up and to the right, then up and to the left 10 times. Repeat this exercise three times.</li>\r\n</ul></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Bed Time Tips', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'bed-time-tips-2', '', '', '2015-09-14 08:41:33', '2015-09-14 08:41:33', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?page_id=1113', 0, 'page', '', 0),
