(1142, 1, '2015-09-15 01:49:25', '2015-09-15 01:49:25', '<div class="inn_contant">\n<h3>FAQ''S ABOUT SLEEP APNOEA</h3>\n<h3>GETTING A GOOD NIGHT''S SLEEP<h3>\n<h4>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA - FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h4>\n[su_accordion]\n      [su_spoiler title=" How severe must sleep apnoea be to require treatment?" style="fancy"] For any type of apnoea to be considered of importance it must be at least 10 seconds in duration or longer. Specialists usually consider 5 or more of such apnoeas per hour to be of possible clinical significance (less than 5 per hour is normal). [/su_spoiler]\n[su_accordion]\n      [su_spoiler title=" How do I know if I have it?" style="fancy"] One of the best people to help you answer this question is your bed partner. People with sleep apnoea generally have the following symptoms:\n<ul>\n	<li>Loud, frequent snoring,</li>\n\n	<li>Poor daytime concentration,</li>\n\n	<li>Irritability and mood changes</li>\n\n	<li>Daytime sleepiness, fatigue and tiredness,</li>\n\n	<li>Impotence and reduced sex drive,</li>\n\n	<li>Need to frequently go to the toilet at night,</li>\n\n	<li>Episodes of gasping, snorting or choking during sleep,</li>\n\n	<li>Lack of energy and endurance.</ul></li>\n\n\n [/su_spoiler]\n[su_accordion]\n      [su_spoiler title=" If I were awakening in the night and having all these symptoms, wouldn''t I be aware of it?" style="fancy"] Probably not. Most people with Sleep Apnoea are unaware that they wake up to breathe many times during the night. Many become accustomed to these brief interruptions but they are significant enough to disrupt the sleep pattern. That''s why they feel sleepy when they are awake. A majority of Sleep Apnoea sufferers go through most of their lives without knowing they suffer this condition. [/su_spoiler]\n[su_accordion]\n      [su_spoiler title=" What should I do if I think I may have sleep apnoea?" style="fancy"] If you suspect you could be suffering from Sleep Apnoea, you are best talking to your doctor who might recommend you visit a Otolaryngologist (ENT - "Ear, Nose, & Throat" doctor), pulmonologist, or sleep disorders expert. [/su_spoiler]\n[su_accordion]\n      [su_spoiler title=" What should I do if I think I may have sleep apnoea?" style="fancy"] If you suspect you could be suffering from Sleep Apnoea, you are best talking to your doctor who might recommend you visit a Otolaryngologist (ENT - "Ear, Nose, & Throat" doctor), pulmonologist, or sleep disorders expert. [/su_spoiler]\n</div>', 'FAQ''s About Sleep Apnoea', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1140-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 01:49:25', '2015-09-15 01:49:25', '', 1140, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/1140-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
