(1158, 1, '2015-09-15 02:34:45', '2015-09-15 02:34:45', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<h3>GETTING A GOOD NIGHT''S SLEEP</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA - PROCESS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Do you feel lethargic at work? Irritable? Lacking in energy?</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you experience any of the symptoms generally associated with Obstructive Sleep Apnoea, don''t take them lightly. Sleep Apnoea is a serious condition that can be easily diagnosed and should be treated by a certified physician.\r\n\r\n<h4>Diagnosing Sleep Apnoea<h4>\r\n\r\nPrior to diagnosing the condition, the physician will need to know your symptoms, as well as any circumstances and significant changes in your life that might be contributing to it - including, whether you have recently put on weight or stopped exercising.\r\n\r\n<h4>Sleep Apnoea can be diagnosed using an in-lab sleep study or a home sleep test.</h4>\r\n\r\nYou may also need to keep a sleep diary for two weeks describing your sleep patterns, including what time you went to bed each night, when you woke up in the morning and how many times you woke up each night.\r\n\r\nPolysomnographic testing - whether conducted in a lab or at home - is used to help the sleep physician evaluate your problem. While there are other types of screenings that claim to detect sleep apnoea accurately, none is as reliable as polysomnographic testing. Beware of any commercial apps or other devices not recommended by a qualified physician.\r\n\r\nIf you are diagnosed with sleep apnoea, your doctor will discuss your treatment options with you.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Treating Sleep Apnoea</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\nTreating sleep apnoea starts with changes to your lifestyle, including losing weight and cutting down on alcohol and quitting smoking. Any other contributing medical or surgical conditions such as low production of thyroid hormone and large tonsils should be corrected.\r\n\r\n<h4>Two treatments are generally used to treat OSA:</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Nasal continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP)</h4>\r\n\r\nA device that pumps air under pressure into the airway, keeping the windpipe open during sleep. Unfortunately, a significant number of people with sleep apnoea find the mask difficult to tolerate.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Mandibular Advancement Splints (Mouthguards)</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\nMandibular repositioning appliances reposition and maintain the lower jaw in a forward position during sleep. This opens the upper airway and repositions the lower jaw and tongue in a more forward position away from the throat.\r\n\r\nDental Splints are comfortable and easy to wear and most people find that it only takes a couple of weeks to become acclimatised to wearing them.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Sleep Apnoea Treatment Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1111-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 02:34:45', '2015-09-15 02:34:45', '', 1111, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/1111-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
