(1161, 1, '2015-09-15 02:50:02', '2015-09-15 02:50:02', '<div class="inn_vide inn_contant">\r\n<div class="col-md-8 "><iframe class="img-thumbnail" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8XH0-kzg8jw?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;controls=1&amp;autohide=1" width="100%" height="280" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-4 inn_page_invs">\r\n<div class="image-logo"><img src="http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/invs_img.jpg" alt="invs_img" width="200" height="50" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-99" /></div>\r\n<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<h3>THE CLEAR WAY</h3>\r\nTO A PERFECTLY\r\nSTRAIGHT SMILE\r\nINVISALIGN</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12">\r\n<h3>THE SMILE YOU''VE ALWAYS DREAMED OF WITH INVISALIGN</h3>\r\nHave you been hiding your smile because you fear othersâ€™ negative reactions? Are you not confident about the way your teeth look?\r\n\r\nIf youâ€™d like a straighter, more beautiful smile without going through traditional orthodontic treatments, Invisalign may be the answer for you.\r\n<h4>What is Invisalign?</h4>\r\nInvisalign is a revolutionary cosmetic dental treatment that uses a series of removable clear aligners (or invisible braces) to gradually straighten your teeth.\r\nIt is a far more comfortable and a lot less intrusive method than traditional orthodontic treatments. With Invisalign, you can achieve the smile of your dreams without anyone noticing youâ€™re undergoing a dental treatment.\r\n<h4>What are the benefits of Invisalign?</h4>\r\n<ul class="list-inline">\r\n	<li>Invisalign is ideal for those who have always wanted a better smile but have been putting off orthodontic treatments because of the social stigma associated with braces.</li>\r\n	<li>The durable, transparent thermoplastic material of the Invisalign aligners make them almost impossible to see and as such, a much more discreet alternative to orthodontic treatments.</li>\r\n	<li>Being completely removable, it is easy to maintain the daily oral hygiene routine needed to reduce the chance of plaque build-up, tooth decay and gum disease.</li>\r\n	<li>These invisible braces donâ€™t rely on traditional metal appliances, so food and plaque are not trapped on the surface of the teeth.</li>\r\n	<li>It is a surprisingly fast treatment, with most of our patients requiring approximately less than a year to transform their smile and be able to display their beautiful new look.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>YOUR INVISALIGN TREATMENT</h4>\r\nDuring your initial consultation at Broadway Dentalâ€™s Sydney Clinic, Dr Yassmin will gain an understanding of your current situation, and explore your goals to determine if Invisalign is suitable for you. Should this be the case, Dr Yassmin will then begin by taking detailed impressions of your teeth. These will then be digitised to create a computerised 3D image of your smile from which, Dr Yassmin will be able to determine the precise movements needed to create the best results. Subsequently, your custom-made invisible braces will be crafted according to your individual treatment plan.\r\nThe number of aligners you will need will depend on your needs and goals however, a full Invisalign treatment typically involves the use of 18 to 36 aligners, and it takes around 9 to 18 months.\r\n<h4>LIVING WITH INVISALIGN</h4>\r\nDuring your treatment, you will wear each aligner for around two weeks, day and night, with small breaks for eating, brushing and flossing your teeth, and the occasional time off for special events. After two weeks, you will then switch to the next aligner which, will move your teeth a little more.\r\nWe will ask you to come in for a check-up every 4-6 weeks so that we can monitor your progress and provide you with your next set of aligners.\r\nThroughout your treatment, you should notice small movements as the invisible braces gradually move your teeth to create an even, healthy and very attractive smile.\r\nTo find out how Invisalign can help you achieve a Hollywood smile, call us today on (02) 9281 0100 or via email.\r\n\r\n<h4>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h4>\r\n\r\n[su_accordion]\r\n  [su_spoiler title="How does Invisalign work?" style="fancy"]  The aligners in the Invisalign apply consistent, controlled force to individual teeth, gently moving them into their new desired position.\r\n\r\nInvisalign differs from traditional braces in that it actually controls the amount of force applied to each tooth and this reduces the length of the treatment in comparison with traditional orthodontics. [/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n  [su_spoiler title="Spoiler title" style="fancy"] Studies show that out of the 1.5 million people who have had or are having Invisalign treatment, 98% of them are satisfied with the results.However, itâ€™s important to remember that Invisalign cannot treat all orthodontic conditions such as severe over or underbites, severely tipped teeth, numerous missing teeth, or unerupted teeth.\r\n\r\nTo find out whether Invisalign is right for you, talk to the team at Broadway Dental on (02) 9281 0100 or via email. [/su_spoiler]\r\n  [su_spoiler title="What does Invisalign look like?" style="fancy"]The clear, strong, non-toxic plastic material Invisalign aligners are manufactured with, make them very difficult to see when worn. Besides, having been custom-made specifically for each patient according to their treatment plan, aligners fit very neatly to the teeth. [/su_spoiler]\r\n   [su_spoiler title="How long does Invisalign treatment take?" style="fancy"] Treatment times vary but on average, patients achieve straighter teeth with Invisalign in around twelve to fourteen months, four months less than traditional braces.[/su_spoiler]\r\n    [su_spoiler title="Is Invisalign painful? " style="fancy"]Wearing the Invisalign aligners is generally far more comfortable than wearing traditional braces. Minor discomfort may be experienced initially and for a few days every time a new aligner is used. This slight feeling of pressure is a sign aligners are doing their job and moving the teeth into the desired position.\r\nAny discomfort is usually relieved in a few days. [/su_spoiler]\r\n      [su_spoiler title="How much does Invisalign cost?" style="fancy"] The cost of an Invisalign treatment depends on individual circumstances but for most of our patients at Broadway Dental, the cost of a full treatment ranges between $3000 and $10,000.After our initial consultation weâ€™ll be able to provide you with a treatment plan detailing all costs for your specific needs. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[/su_accordion]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Invisalign', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 02:50:02', '2015-09-15 02:50:02', '', 95, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1162, 1, '2015-09-15 02:51:17', '2015-09-15 02:51:17', '<div class="inn_vide inn_contant">\r\n<div class="col-md-8 "><iframe class="cont_map" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8XH0-kzg8jw?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;controls=1&amp;autohide=1" width="100%" height="280" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-4 inn_page_invs">\r\n<div class="image-logo"><img src="http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/invs_img.jpg" alt="invs_img" width="200" height="50" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-99" /></div>\r\n<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<h3>THE CLEAR WAY</h3>\r\nTO A PERFECTLY\r\nSTRAIGHT SMILE\r\nINVISALIGN</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12">\r\n<h3>THE SMILE YOU''VE ALWAYS DREAMED OF WITH INVISALIGN</h3>\r\nHave you been hiding your smile because you fear othersâ€™ negative reactions? Are you not confident about the way your teeth look?\r\n\r\nIf youâ€™d like a straighter, more beautiful smile without going through traditional orthodontic treatments, Invisalign may be the answer for you.\r\n<h4>What is Invisalign?</h4>\r\nInvisalign is a revolutionary cosmetic dental treatment that uses a series of removable clear aligners (or invisible braces) to gradually straighten your teeth.\r\nIt is a far more comfortable and a lot less intrusive method than traditional orthodontic treatments. With Invisalign, you can achieve the smile of your dreams without anyone noticing youâ€™re undergoing a dental treatment.\r\n<h4>What are the benefits of Invisalign?</h4>\r\n<ul class="list-inline">\r\n	<li>Invisalign is ideal for those who have always wanted a better smile but have been putting off orthodontic treatments because of the social stigma associated with braces.</li>\r\n	<li>The durable, transparent thermoplastic material of the Invisalign aligners make them almost impossible to see and as such, a much more discreet alternative to orthodontic treatments.</li>\r\n	<li>Being completely removable, it is easy to maintain the daily oral hygiene routine needed to reduce the chance of plaque build-up, tooth decay and gum disease.</li>\r\n	<li>These invisible braces donâ€™t rely on traditional metal appliances, so food and plaque are not trapped on the surface of the teeth.</li>\r\n	<li>It is a surprisingly fast treatment, with most of our patients requiring approximately less than a year to transform their smile and be able to display their beautiful new look.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>YOUR INVISALIGN TREATMENT</h4>\r\nDuring your initial consultation at Broadway Dentalâ€™s Sydney Clinic, Dr Yassmin will gain an understanding of your current situation, and explore your goals to determine if Invisalign is suitable for you. Should this be the case, Dr Yassmin will then begin by taking detailed impressions of your teeth. These will then be digitised to create a computerised 3D image of your smile from which, Dr Yassmin will be able to determine the precise movements needed to create the best results. Subsequently, your custom-made invisible braces will be crafted according to your individual treatment plan.\r\nThe number of aligners you will need will depend on your needs and goals however, a full Invisalign treatment typically involves the use of 18 to 36 aligners, and it takes around 9 to 18 months.\r\n<h4>LIVING WITH INVISALIGN</h4>\r\nDuring your treatment, you will wear each aligner for around two weeks, day and night, with small breaks for eating, brushing and flossing your teeth, and the occasional time off for special events. After two weeks, you will then switch to the next aligner which, will move your teeth a little more.\r\nWe will ask you to come in for a check-up every 4-6 weeks so that we can monitor your progress and provide you with your next set of aligners.\r\nThroughout your treatment, you should notice small movements as the invisible braces gradually move your teeth to create an even, healthy and very attractive smile.\r\nTo find out how Invisalign can help you achieve a Hollywood smile, call us today on (02) 9281 0100 or via email.\r\n\r\n<h4>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h4>\r\n\r\n[su_accordion]\r\n  [su_spoiler title="How does Invisalign work?" style="fancy"]  The aligners in the Invisalign apply consistent, controlled force to individual teeth, gently moving them into their new desired position.\r\n\r\nInvisalign differs from traditional braces in that it actually controls the amount of force applied to each tooth and this reduces the length of the treatment in comparison with traditional orthodontics. [/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n  [su_spoiler title="Spoiler title" style="fancy"] Studies show that out of the 1.5 million people who have had or are having Invisalign treatment, 98% of them are satisfied with the results.However, itâ€™s important to remember that Invisalign cannot treat all orthodontic conditions such as severe over or underbites, severely tipped teeth, numerous missing teeth, or unerupted teeth.\r\n\r\nTo find out whether Invisalign is right for you, talk to the team at Broadway Dental on (02) 9281 0100 or via email. [/su_spoiler]\r\n  [su_spoiler title="What does Invisalign look like?" style="fancy"]The clear, strong, non-toxic plastic material Invisalign aligners are manufactured with, make them very difficult to see when worn. Besides, having been custom-made specifically for each patient according to their treatment plan, aligners fit very neatly to the teeth. [/su_spoiler]\r\n   [su_spoiler title="How long does Invisalign treatment take?" style="fancy"] Treatment times vary but on average, patients achieve straighter teeth with Invisalign in around twelve to fourteen months, four months less than traditional braces.[/su_spoiler]\r\n    [su_spoiler title="Is Invisalign painful? " style="fancy"]Wearing the Invisalign aligners is generally far more comfortable than wearing traditional braces. Minor discomfort may be experienced initially and for a few days every time a new aligner is used. This slight feeling of pressure is a sign aligners are doing their job and moving the teeth into the desired position.\r\nAny discomfort is usually relieved in a few days. [/su_spoiler]\r\n      [su_spoiler title="How much does Invisalign cost?" style="fancy"] The cost of an Invisalign treatment depends on individual circumstances but for most of our patients at Broadway Dental, the cost of a full treatment ranges between $3000 and $10,000.After our initial consultation weâ€™ll be able to provide you with a treatment plan detailing all costs for your specific needs. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[/su_accordion]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Invisalign', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 02:51:17', '2015-09-15 02:51:17', '', 95, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1163, 1, '2015-09-15 02:54:38', '2015-09-15 02:54:38', '<h1>WHAT IS ALL ON 4 DENTAL IMPLANT</h1>\r\n\r\n									<p><img width="277" height="184" data-id="2666" src="http://broadwaydental.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/a_03.jpg" alt="a_03" class="alignleft  img-thumbnail">What is All On 4 dental implant?</p>\r\n<p>The All-On-4 system offered at our Dental Clinic is a new innovation in implant dentistry, which brings a dental prosthesis and dental implants together.</p>\r\n<p>A dental implant is a fine titanium screw or rod placed into the jaw bone during a minor surgical procedure to replace a missing tooth root. Titanium is a strong bio-compatible alloy and has been used successfully in reconstructive medicine for many years as it naturally integrates with bone.</p>\r\n<p>Previously, a single dental implant was placed vertically and used to replace a single tooth or support a dental bridge of up to three teeth. To support an entire upper or lower arch of teeth, up to eight dental implants were necessary.</p>\r\n<p>The All-On-4 System enables you to have a set of upper or lower prosthetic teeth permanently secured, often with as few as four dental implants.</p>\r\n<p>The treatment is made possible because two of the implants are slightly longer than traditional dental implants. They are also placed at an acute angle at the front of the mouth where your jaw bone is denser and stronger, and provides the greatest support for your prosthesis.</p>\r\n\r\n									\r\n										<a title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" class="book-now" href="http://www.broadwaydental.com.au/make-an-appointment/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n\r\n									\r\n', 'Whats is All On 4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '187-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 02:54:38', '2015-09-15 02:54:38', '', 187, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/187-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1164, 1, '2015-09-15 04:58:21', '2015-09-15 04:58:21', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n \r\n[su_accordion]\r\n      [su_spoiler title="Q. Is implant surgery painful?" style="fancy"] A. With various anaesthetic options available your procedure can be completed quickly and with little to no discomfort. We can also provide IV Sedation, sometimes called Sleep Dentistry, which is completely safe and where you are in a deeply relaxed state.  [/su_spoiler]\r\n  [su_spoiler title="Q. What''s the difference between the All-On-4 System and MDI?" style="fancy"] A. With the All-On-4 System, the four dental implants are placed strategically at the front and back of your mouth. This provides maximum stability and allows the dentist to securely install the fixed bridge. \r\nThese MDI (Mini Dental Implants) are a much finer implant and have a ball head with a rubber O-ring. This allows a prosthesis to lock into place and also be removed. Mini Dental Implants are also shorter and placed vertically Just as importantly, MDI do not integrate into the bone. This means the MDI is a temporary solution - one that can only be used with overdenture systems. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[su_spoiler title="Q. Why replace missing teeth?" style="fancy"] A. When you have missing teeth, whether it''s one or an entire arch, it can have a detrimental effect on your oral and general health. If you have teeth on either side of a gap they can move out of alignment and into the space, making them harder to clean and increasing the risk of gum disease. Missing teeth can also result in your jaw bone losing density and volume. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[su_spoiler title="Q. How successful is the All-On-4 System?" style="fancy"] A. The All-On-4 System offered at Broadway Dental enjoys a very high success rate with published statistics showing a greater than 98 per cent on the lower arch and 94 percent on the upper arch. The high success rate is attributed to how the implants are placed, bone density and on-going oral hygiene appointments every six months to ensure optimal gum and oral health is achieved and maintained. [/su_spoiler]\r\n[/su_accordion]\r\n</div>', 'FAQ''s', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '182-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 04:58:21', '2015-09-15 04:58:21', '', 182, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/182-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1165, 1, '2015-09-15 05:05:34', '2015-09-15 05:05:34', ' <div class="inn_contant">\r\n<h3>DENTAL CROWNS: RESTORING YOUR TEETH AND ORAL HEALTH</h3>\r\nDental crowns (or caps) are designed to cover or ''cap'' a tooth to restore it to its normal shape and size, strengthening and improving its appearance.\r\n\r\n<h4>When are Dental Crowns used?</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>When a tooth has broken down to the extent that fillings will no longer solve the problem,</li>\r\n	<li>For heavily restored teeth that are vulnerable to fracture,</li>\r\n	<li>In the case of cracked, broken, badly shaped or discoloured teeth, or</li>\r\n	<li>In teeth that have undergone root canal therapy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>What are dental crowns made of?</h4>\r\n\r\nThey can be made from a variety of materials including porcelain, metal or both.\r\nPorcelain dental crowns tend to be preferred because they are extremely strong while mimicking the translucency of natural tooth enamel.\r\n\r\nDr Yassmin''s team at Broadway Dental will custom-make your Dental Crown to fit perfectly well over your prepared tooth structure.\r\n</div>', 'Dental Crowns', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '212-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 05:05:34', '2015-09-15 05:05:34', '', 212, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/212-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1166, 1, '2015-09-15 05:24:26', '2015-09-15 05:24:26', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\n<h3>Achieve Straighter and Whiter Teeth with Porcelain Veneers</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Would you like to have a gorgeous white smile?</h4>\r\n\r\nOf course you would!\r\n\r\nThen, porcelain veneers could be the answer.\r\n\r\nConstructed from strong, high quality porcelains that closely mimic the many shades and translucencies found in natural teeth, each Dental Veneer consists of a thin porcelain shell that fits neatly over the front surfaces of your teeth.\r\n\r\nOnce in position it can help create a flawless smile, specifically designed to match your preferred look.\r\n\r\n<h4>When should Porcelain Veneers be used?</h4>\r\n\r\n<strong>After a careful assessment, Dr Yassmin might recommend the use of Porcelain Veneers to hide a number of imperfections, such as:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Discoloured or stained teeth that will not respond to conventional tooth whitening treatments,</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Minor chips or cracks to teeth, and to replace sections of teeth that have worn away,</li><li>To lengthen or change the shape of teeth,</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n	<li>To recontoure irregularly shaped teeth.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n	<li>To close or minimise gaps in between teeth,</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>To correct teeth that are just slightly out of alignment and where it isn''t necessary to have orthodontic treatment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>How do I get Porcelain Veneers?</h4>\r\n\r\nDuring your initial consultation at Broadway Dental''s Sydney, Dr Yassmin will discuss your overall goals and assess your suitability to have Porcelain Veneers fitted.\r\n\r\nThe next appointment will be to prepare your teeth. Dental veneers are minimally invasive, but it''s usually necessary for Dr Yassmin to remove a small amount of tooth enamel from the front surfaces of your teeth. This helps ensure the finished appearance is natural and aesthetically pleasing. Once your teeth have been shaped for the veneers, an impression is taken for the dental laboratory to have them customised.\r\n\r\nThis process generally takes a couple of weeks depending on the number of veneers required. During this time we will protect your teeth with temporary veneers, providing you with a preview of your new smile!\r\n\r\nThe actual Porcelain Veneers will be fitted during your next visit. It might be necessary to make some minor adjustments to get the fit absolutely precise before they are permanently bonded in position.\r\n\r\n<h4>Using Veneers as part of a Smile Makeover</h4>\r\n\r\n<strong>Dental Veneers are often used in conjunction with other treatments as part of a smile makeover, including:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dental Crowns,</li>\r\n	<li>Teeth Whitening procedures,</li>\r\n	<li>Invisalign teeth straightening treatment to help perfect a beautifully aligned smile.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Are Dental Veneers suitable for everyone?</h4>\r\n\r\nVeneers are suitable for most people.\r\n\r\nHowever, it''s important that teeth are healthy and strong and there are no signs of gum disease prior to fitting any dental veneers.\r\n\r\nFor teeth that have already been filled or are rather weak, Dr Yassmin may suggest alternative procedures such as dental crowns which, will help perfect your smile while restoring strength to your teeth.\r\n\r\n<h4>Are there any disadvantages to having Dental Veneers?</h4>\r\n\r\nDental Veneers are an excellent way to help improve your smile. However, it''s important to be aware that this is generally a non-reversible treatment as it''s almost always necessary to remove some of the enamel of the tooth to make room for the veneers.\r\n\r\nOnly in cases when the removal of the enamel is not necessary may the treatment be reversed.\r\n\r\n<h4>How do I look after my dental veneers?</h4>\r\n\r\nDental veneers are very easy to look after as you simply need to brush and floss them exactly as you would your natural teeth.\r\n\r\nHowever, remember that regular check-ups and professional cleanings by the team at Broadway Dental will help keep your teeth and gums healthy and strong and prolong the life of your veneers.\r\n\r\n<h4>I grind my teeth - can I still have veneers?</h4>\r\n\r\nTooth grinding or Bruxism is a common issue and if not treated could chip or fracture your veneers. Ask us about having a custom-made night guard to help protect your veneers and your natural teeth against damage.\r\n\r\n<h4>How long will my porcelain veneers last?</h4>\r\n\r\nWith a proper home dental routine and professional dental care, your veneers should last 10 years or more but they will eventually need replacing.\r\n</div>', 'Porcelain Dental Veneers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-15 05:24:26', '2015-09-15 05:24:26', '', 210, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/210-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
