(1264, 1, '2015-09-28 07:15:21', '2015-09-28 07:15:21', '<div class="treatments-provided">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Photos and Radiographic records</li>\r\n	<li>Photos and radiographic records were taken to allow accurate assessment of the existing dentition (development and arrangement of teeth in her mouth) and to give Tracey a visual view of the treatment needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Preventative care (Dental prophylaxis)</li>\r\n	<li>Deep scaling and polishing to remove the buildup of heavy plaque (also known as calculus and tartar) and staining on Tracey''s teeth, helping prevent cavities and gum disease</li>\r\n	<li>Oral hygiene routine - Cariscreen and caries free rinse program. Custom trays of GC tooth mousse were created for home use, which will help prevent tooth decay (that can lead to cavities, pain, tooth loss and infection) and minimise intrinsic staining (white specs on teeth).</li>\r\n	<li>White fillings - To rejuvenate her teeth, broken amalgam fillings were replaced with white fillings for a more natural, comfortable smile. Made from premise(composite) these new fillings are also free from any trace of mercury.</li>\r\n	<li>Aesthetic Recontouring - Reshaping the teeth by adding white filling material and gently discing teeth.</li>\r\n	<li>Teeth whitening - BriteSmile whitening system was used to whiten Tracey''s teeth. Custom trays were also made to give Tracey a whitening maintenance program to take home to help sustain her whiter smile.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a class="book-now" title="Make an Appointment with Dentist Sydney" href="http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/contact-us/">book your consultation today</a>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>', '10 Years Younger in 10 days', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '155-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-28 07:15:21', '2015-09-28 07:15:21', '', 155, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/155-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1265, 1, '2015-09-28 07:29:37', '2015-09-28 07:29:37', '<div class="inn_contant">\r\nElecting to have veneers made for your smile is an exciting time. Veneers help your teeth look straighter, whiter and everything you want them to be. When you expect this much out of your smile, you want to choose treatments that utilise only the highest quality of materials. Materials that looks natural, beautiful and strong.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nVeneers can be used to correct teeth that look:\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Crooked\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Widely-spaced\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Crowded\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Chipped, worn or broken\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Stained / discoloured\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Misshaped\r\n\r\nTwo of the most common materials used for veneers include porcelain and resin. Each type of veneer has its own advantages that make it the choice option for certain patients, but there is a clear-cut difference between one type of veneer and the other.\r\n\r\n \r\nPorcelain Veneers\r\n\r\nPorcelain veneers are made in a dental lab using state-of-the-art techniques to create restorations that are beautiful yet appears natural at the same time. The thin, semi-translucent material is bonded over your tooth giving you a perfect-looking smile that looks like you were born with it. Since porcelain provides superior aesthetics, it is often the preferred material for patients undergoing complete smile makeovers or who need several teeth restored at a time. If youâ€™ve decided that porcelain veneers are your best option, Dr Yassmin will gently adjust the shape of your natural teeth and take an impression of them. Because the handcrafted process of veneers is so precise, it may take up to two weeks for your permanent veneers to be ready. In the meantime, a set of temporary veneers are worn, giving you a good idea of what your treatment will look like before itâ€™s even finished. Once your permanent veneers are ready, youâ€™ll return for a simple visit where each of the veneers is bonded into place.\r\n\r\n \r\nResin Veneers\r\n\r\nResin veneers are made of the same type of material that is used in white fillings. Rather than being made in a laboratory or by a technician, these veneers are made and placed in one appointment by your dentist. They are a more affordable veneer option for patients in need of cosmetic treatments. Similar to having a filling made, the resin is placed onto your tooth and formed into the desired shape. Using a curing light, the composite material is hardened into place. Only one appointment is needed. Because opaque resin does not feature many of the natural similarities of other materials, they are typically best for smaller cases when correcting only one or two teeth at a time.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSome things to keep in mind when youâ€™ve elected to have veneers:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nHow many veneers do you need?\r\n\r\nWhat are you trying to achieve?\r\n\r\nWhat is your budget?\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBroadway Dental has provided thousands of dental veneers to our patients in the Sydney and the surrounding areas. We invite you to visit us to learn more about how dental veneers can enhance your smile. Feel free to look through some of our before and after photographs and discuss your specific concerns or treatment with Dr Yassmin. We look forward to meeting you!\r\n</div>', 'Choosing the Right Type of Dental Veneers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'choosing-the-right-type-of-dental-veneers', '', '', '2015-09-28 07:34:06', '2015-09-28 07:34:06', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Broadwaydental/php/?p=1265', 0, 'post', '', 0),
